1
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:30,630
窈窕淑女

2
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:35,670
主演：奥黛丽赫本

3
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:39,940
雷克斯哈里逊

4
00:03:06,730 --> 00:03:10,390
编剧：亚兰艾勒纳

5
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:16,500
制片：杰克华纳

6
00:03:16,610 --> 00:03:23,450
导演：乔治库克

7
00:04:55,910 --> 00:04:58,070
佛雷狄，去找部车来！
Freddy, go and find a cab.

8
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,870
你要我得肺炎吗？
Do you want me to catch pneumonia?

9
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:15,330
别楞在那里，佛雷狄 去找部车来
Don't just stand there, Freddy. Go and find a cab.

10
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,790
好的，我去叫车
All right, l'll get one. l'll get it.

11
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,840
走路小心点，亲爱的 走路小心点！
Look where you're goin', dear. Look where you're goin'!

12
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,210
我很抱歉
l'm so sorry.

13
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:42,540
两束紫罗兰掉到泥里 一天的辛苦就完了
Two bunches o' violets trod in the mud. A full day's wages.

14
00:05:42,650 --> 00:05:46,890
佛雷狄，去叫车 是的，母亲
-Freddy, go and find a cab. -Yes, Mother.

15
00:05:49,860 --> 00:05:51,690
他是你的儿子吗？
Oh, he's your son, is he?

16
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:54,090
如果你尽到一个作母亲的责任
lf you'd done your duty by him as a mother should...

17
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:58,140
你就应该为此事赔偿 而非置之不理啊
you wouldn't let 'im spoil a poor girl's flow'rs and then run away without payin'.

18
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,140
去作你的生意，小女孩
Oh, go about your business, my girl.

19
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,140
你一点都不愿意赔偿？
And you wouldn't go off without payin', either.

20
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:06,170
两束紫罗兰掉到泥里
Two bunches o' violets trod in the mud.

21
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:11,880
先生，雨会停吗？
Oh, sir, is there any sign of it stopping?

22
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:14,280
恐怕不会 现在比刚刚下得还要大
l'm afraid not. lt's worse than before.

23
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,910
如果下得更大 那就是快停的征兆了
lf it's worse, it's a sign it's nearly over.

24
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:19,820
开心点，长官 买一束可怜女孩的花吧
Cheer up, Capt'n, buy a flow'r off a poor girl.

25
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,320
很抱歉，我没零钱
l'm sorry, l haven't any change.

26
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:24,020
我可以找钱给你 来吧，一朵才两便士
l can change 'alf a crown. Here, take this for tuppence.

27
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:26,600
我告诉过你，我很抱歉 等一下
l told you, l'm awfully sorry. Wait a minute.

28
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:29,900
有了，三便士，对你可能有用
Oh, yes. Here's three hapence, if that's any use to you.

29
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,370
谢谢，先生
Thank you, sir.

30
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,680
听着，你小心点 最好给他一束花
Here, you be careful. Better give 'im a flower for it.

31
00:06:41,780 --> 00:06:46,480
柱子后面有个家伙 把你所说的话都记下来了
There's a bloke here behind that pillar... takin' down every blessed word you're sayin'.

32
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,820
我跟他说话又没做错什么事
l ain't done nothin' wrong by speakin' to the gentleman.

33
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:57,950
我有权利在这里卖花 我是人格高尚的女孩，帮帮我
l've a right t' sell flow'rs if l keep off the curb. l'm a respectable girl, so help me.

34
00:06:58,060 --> 00:07:01,230
我只请他买花又没跟他说话
l never spoke to him except to ask him to buy a flow'r off me.

35
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:04,190
为何如此吵？ 有个侦探纪录她的话
-What's all the bloomin' noise? -There's a tec takin' her down.

36
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,100
我是自立维生
l'm makin' an honest livin'.

37
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,000
是谁这么吵闹？
Who's doing all that shouting?

38
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,140
先生，别让他起诉我 你不知道这会对我有多大影响
Sir, don't let 'im charge me. You dunno what it means to me.

39
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:16,980
他们会取消我的资格 只因我在街上跟男士说话
They'll take away me character and drive me on the streets... for speakin' t' gentlemen.

40
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:21,780
好了...谁要伤害你，傻女孩？ 你以为我是谁啊？
There, there, there. Who's hurting you, you silly girl? What'd you take me for?

41
00:07:21,850 --> 00:07:23,480
我对圣经发誓我并没有说话
On my Bible oath, l never spoke a word.

42
00:07:23,590 --> 00:07:25,680
闭嘴！...我像警察吗？
Shut up! Shut up! Do l look like a policeman?

43
00:07:25,790 --> 00:07:29,090
你为何记下我的话？ 我认识你可以这样吗？
Then what'd ya take down me words for? 'Ow do l know you took me down right?

44
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:31,690
给我看你写了我些什么事情
You just show me what you wrote ab'ut me.

45
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,670
这不是正确的写字方法 我看不懂
That ain't proper writin'. l can't read it.

46
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:42,740
我看得懂
l can.

47
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:47,010
开心点，长官 买一束可怜女孩的花吧
''l say, Capt'n, now buy a flow'r off a poor girl.''

48
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:52,670
只因为我叫他长官吗
Oh, it's cause l called him ''Capt'n.''

49
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:56,620
我无意伤人，先生 别让他因这个字而起诉我
l meant no 'arm. Sir, don't let him lay a charge against me for a word like that.

50
00:07:56,720 --> 00:08:01,030
起诉？我不会让他起诉你 先生，如果你是侦探
l'll make no charge. Really, sir, if you are a detective...

51
00:08:01,090 --> 00:08:05,260
除非我要求，你不需要怕我 被这小女孩欺负而保护我
you needn't begin protecting me against molestation from young women... until l ask you.

52
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:07,590
任何人都看得出来 这女孩伤不了人的
Anyone could tell the girl meant no harm.

53
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:10,730
他不是侦探 看他穿的皮靴就知道他是绅士
He ain't no tec. He's a gentleman. Look at his boots.

54
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,930
你们怎么都是来自塞西？
How are all your people down at Selsey?

55
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,510
谁告诉你我们来自塞西？
Who told you my people come from Selsey?

56
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:16,940
你别管，他们是的
Never mind, they do.

57
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:21,800
你怎会到这么遥远的东部来？ 你来自利索格罗夫
How do you come to be up so far east? You were born in Lisson Grove.

58
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:26,170
我离开利索格罗夫 又有何不对？
Oh, what 'arm is there in my leavin' Lisson Grove?

59
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:29,350
那里连猪都活不下去 我一星期得付四到六元的房租
lt weren't fit for pigs to live. l had to pay four and six a week.

60
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:31,180
去住你喜欢住的地方 但别再吵了！
Live where you like but stop that noise!

61
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:34,820
冷静点！他不会抓你的 你有权利住你想住的地方！
Come, come, he can't touch you. You've a right to live where you please.

62
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:36,790
我是个好女孩，真的
l'm a good girl, l am.

63
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,760
你知我从那儿来的吗？ 霍克斯顿
-Where do l come from? -Hawkestone.

64
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:42,590
真的是耶，我的天啊 你无所不知啊
Who said l didn't? Blimey, you know everything, you do.

65
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:45,930
先生 你能帮我找部计程车吗？
You, sir, do you think you could find me a taxi?

66
00:08:46,140 --> 00:08:50,510
女士，雨停了 你可以搭公车会汉普顿
Madam, it's stopped raining. You can get a motorbus to Hampton Court.

67
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,440
那是你住的地方吧？
That's where you live, isn't it?

68
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:54,240
真是没礼貌！
What an impertinence!

69
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:58,050
如果你要算命 告诉我他打哪儿来
Tell 'im where he comes from, if you wanta go fortune-telling.

70
00:09:00,350 --> 00:09:06,310
赤尔登罕，哈络，剑桥还有...
Cheltenham, Harrow... Cambridge and...

71
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:09,220
印度？
lndia?

72
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,450
对极了
Quite right.

73
00:09:10,930 --> 00:09:13,230
天啊，他不是侦探 他是个非常爱管事的人
Blimey, he ain't a tec, he's a bloomin' busybody.

74
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:16,160
请问你是以此维生音乐人吗？
Do you do this sort of thing for a living at a music hall?

75
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:18,360
我有考虑过 也许有一天会这样做
l have thought of it. Perhaps l will one day.

76
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:21,770
他不是位绅士 只会欺负可怜的女孩子
He's no gentleman, he ain't, to interfere with a poor girl!

77
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,470
请教你是从事什么工作？
How do you do it, may l ask?

78
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:28,700
语言学，说话的科学 这是我的专业和也是嗜好
Simple phonetics. The science of speech. That's my profession. Also my hobby.

79
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:32,080
每个人都可以从他的土腔 分辨出是爱尔兰人或约克郡人
Anyone can spot an lrishman or a Yorkshireman by his brogue...

80
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,310
我可以分辨出 每隔六哩的不同人
but l can place a man within six miles.

81
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:38,250
在伦敦每隔二哩就会有不同 有时甚至两条街
l can place 'im within two miles in London. Sometimes within two streets.

82
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:41,150
他应该自觉可耻，胆小鬼
Ought to be ashamed of 'imself, unmanly coward.

83
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:43,090
以此维生吗？ 是的
-ls there a living in that? -Oh, yes.

84
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:46,220
就让他忙他自己的事 别管这位可怜的女孩
Let him mind his own business and leave a poor girl alone.

85
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:52,400
女人，马上停止这讨厌的哭声 或是躲到别处去吧！
Cease this detestable boohooing instantly... or else seek the shelter of some other place of worship!

86
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:56,270
我有权待在我喜欢的地方 跟你一样！
l have a right to be here if l like, same as you!

87
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:59,270
发出如此讨厌声音的女人
A woman who utters such disgusting and depressing noises...

88
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:01,900
就没有资格到处走 没有资格生活
has no right to be anywhere, no right to live.

89
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:06,420
记住，你是一个有灵魂的人 并具有口齿清楚的天赋
Remember, you're a human being with a soul... and the divine gift of articulate speech.

90
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:09,820
你的母语是沙士比亚 弥尔顿和圣经的语言
That your native language is the language of Shakespeare and...

91
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:14,060
别像讨厌的傻瓜般 坐在哪儿咆哮
Milton and the Bible. Don't sit there crooning like a bilious pigeon.

92
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:18,760
看看她，下层人士的话语
Look at her, a prisoner of the gutters

93
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,060
她说的每个音节都不适当
Condemned by ev'ry syllable she utters

94
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:29,200
她应该被吊死 因为她无情地谋杀了英语
By right she should be taken out an'hung For the cold-blooded murder Of the English tongue

95
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,840
天啊，这是什么声音！
Heavens, what a sound!

96
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:38,440
这就是英国人民 所谓的小学教育
This is what the British population Calls an element'ry education

97
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,310
先生 你最好举个失败的例子说明
Come, sir, l think you've picked a poor example.

98
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:42,780
要吗？
Did l?

99
00:10:43,390 --> 00:10:47,190
听听看苏活区的人 不发“H”的音
Hear them down in Soho Square Dropping ''Hs '' everywhere

100
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:49,730
照他们喜欢的英语发音
Speaking English any way they like

101
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,530
先生，你上过学吗？
Hey, you, sir, did you go to school?

102
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:54,260
你“以谓”我是傻瓜吗？
What ya tike me for, a fool?

103
00:10:54,370 --> 00:10:56,990
没人教他“以谓” 是要发成“以为”
No one taught him ''take''instead of ''tike''

104
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,740
听约克人说话 更糟的是听康瓦耳人交谈
Hear a Yorkshireman, or worse Hear a Cornishman converse

105
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:04,240
我宁愿去听平调的诗歌
l'd rather hear a choir singing flat

106
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:08,680
如小鸡在粮仓里咯咯叫 就像她一样
Chickens cackling in a barn Just like this one

107
00:11:08,810 --> 00:11:10,280
咯恩！
Garn!

108
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:11,780
咯恩！
Garn!

109
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:15,010
我请教你，先生 这是什么字？
l ask you, sir, what sort of word is that?

110
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:18,280
她总会发出 “奥哦” 和 “咯恩”的声音
lt's ''aoow''and ''garn '' That keep her in her place

111
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:21,320
不是因为她穿破烂衣服 不是因为她的脸很脏
Not her wretched clothes and dirty face

112
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:26,190
为何英国人 不能教小孩如何说话？
Why can't the English Teach their children how to speak?

113
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:29,900
上语言课时很容易区分 现在为时已晚了
This verbal class distinction By now should be antique

114
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:33,570
如果你说话跟她一样 不像现在这样说话
lf you spoke as she does, sir lnstead of the way you do

115
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:36,470
你大概也去卖花了
Why, you might be selling flowers, too

116
00:11:36,610 --> 00:11:37,630
你说什么
l beg your pardon.

117
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:41,140
一个英国人说英语的方式 绝对会影响到他的地位
An Englishman's way of speaking Absolutely classifies him

118
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:44,780
他一讲英语其他人会鄙视他
The moment he talks he makes Some other Englishman despise him

119
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:48,290
我怕我们永远听不到正统语言
One common language l'm afraid we'll never get

120
00:11:48,550 --> 00:11:51,850
为何不好好学英文？
Oh, why can't the English learn to

121
00:11:52,490 --> 00:11:57,260
让我们有顺耳的英语 谁的英语会伤害你的耳朵
Set a good example to people Whose English is painful to your ears

122
00:11:58,130 --> 00:12:01,160
苏格兰和爱尔兰的英语 听了会让你流泪
The Scotch and the lrish Leave you close to tears

123
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:05,730
甚至有些地方正统英语不见了
There even are places Where English completely disappears

124
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,930
在美国 他们很久没使用正统英语了！
Why, in America They haven't used it for years!

125
00:12:10,210 --> 00:12:13,180
为何英国人 不能教小孩说正统英语？
Why can't the English Teach their children how to speak?

126
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:16,880
挪威人学习挪威语 希腊人就教希腊话
Norwegians learn Norwegian The Greeks are taught their Greek

127
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:20,710
在法国每一个法国人 都非常了解他们的语言
ln France every Frenchman Knows his language from ''A '' to ''Z''

128
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:25,320
法国人不注重如何教导 只要发音正确就好
The French don't care What they do actually As long as they pronounce it properly

129
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:29,320
阿拉伯人学阿拉伯语 他们说话速度如闪电般
Arabians learn Arabian With the speed of summer lightning

130
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:32,890
犹太人说希伯来语 说得令人震惊
The Hebrews learn it backwards Which is absolutely frightening

131
00:12:33,430 --> 00:12:36,660
使用正统英语 你们却视为怪物
Use proper English You're regarded as a freak

132
00:12:36,830 --> 00:12:38,960
为何不说正统英语
Oh, why can't the English

133
00:12:40,770 --> 00:12:44,760
为何英语无法说得正确？
Why can't the English learn to speak?

134
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,740
谢谢
Thank you.

135
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:59,260
你看她说的破英语 这种英语将伴随终身吗？
You see this creature with her curbstone English... that'll keep her in the gutter till the end of her days?

136
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:03,850
我训练她六个月后 可以像女公爵般出席大使舞会
Well, sir, in six months l could pass her off as a duchess at an Embassy Ball.

137
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:08,760
我也能让她到需要说 正统英语的地方上班
l could get her a job as a lady's maid or a shop assistant... which requires better English.

138
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:10,630
你在说些什么？
'Ere, what's that you say?

139
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:16,310
你这个烂芭乐 你污辱了这些高贵的建筑物！
Yes, you squashed cabbage leaf! You disgrace to the noble architecture of these columns!

140
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:19,900
你真的冒犯了正统英语！
You incarnate insult to the English language!

141
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:22,940
我可以训练你成为女王
l could pass you off as the Queen of Sheba.

142
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:27,050
你不会相信这些吧，长官？
You don't believe that, Capt'n?

143
00:13:27,190 --> 00:13:30,880
有可能，我还在学印度方言
Anything's possible. l, myself, am a student of lndian dialects.

144
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:35,290
是吗？你认识平克林上校吗 “口语梵文”的作者？
Are you? Do you know Colonel Pickering, the author of Spoken Sanskrit?

145
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:38,730
我就是平克林上校，你是谁？
l am Colonel Pickering. Who are you?

146
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:41,830
我是亨利席根斯 “席根斯的世界字母”作者
l'm Henry Higgins, author of Higgins' Universal Alphabet.

147
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:44,490
我从印度来找你！
l came from lndia to meet you!

148
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,570
我正要去印度找你！
