00:28:36,890 --> 00:28:41,330
我们要请这个小妞坐下 还是丢出窗外？
Should we ask this baggage to sit down... or shall we just throw her out of the window?

306
00:28:41,430 --> 00:28:45,870
我不是小妞 何况我像其他小姐一样会付钱
l won't be called a baggage. Not when l've offered to pay like any lady.

307
00:28:46,670 --> 00:28:48,230
你想要干什么，女孩？
What do you want, my girl?

308
00:28:52,610 --> 00:28:57,380
我想要在花店当专柜小姐
l want to be a lady in a flow'r shop... 'stead of sellin' at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.

309
00:28:57,450 --> 00:29:00,180
除非我举止优雅 否则他们不会请我
But they won't take me unless l can talk more genteel.

310
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:03,740
他说他能教我 所以我来付钱请他教
'E said 'e could teach me. Well, 'ere l am ready to pay 'im.

311
00:29:03,820 --> 00:29:07,050
不是要来占便宜的 他却如此对我
Not asking any favor and he treats me as if l was dirt.

312
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:11,630
我知道你上课的价钱 所以我准备要付钱
l know what lessons cost as well as you do, and l'm ready t' pay.

313
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:15,930
付多少钱？
How much?

314
00:29:16,370 --> 00:29:18,300
你终于说话了
Now you're talkin'.

315
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:22,840
我想你是要补偿 昨晚不该如此摒弃我
l thought you'd come off it for a chance o' gettin' back a bit... of what you chucked at me last night.

316
00:29:22,910 --> 00:29:24,840
其实你很欢迎我，是吗？
You'd had a drop in, 'adn't you, eh?

317
00:29:24,940 --> 00:29:26,140
坐下
Sit down.

318
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:29,370
如果你要表达歉意... 坐下
-lf you're goin' t' make a compliment of it-- -Sit down!

319
00:29:30,450 --> 00:29:32,680
坐下，女孩，照他的话做
Sit down, girl. Do as you're told.

320
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:34,650
贵姓大名？
What's your name?

321
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,710
伊莱莎杜立特尔
Eliza Doolittle.

322
00:29:37,290 --> 00:29:39,880
你不坐下吗，杜立特尔小姐？
Won't you sit down, Miss Doolittle?

323
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:45,120
我不介意坐下
l don't mind if l do.

324
00:29:48,730 --> 00:29:51,860
你打算要给我多少学费？
How much do you propose to pay me for these lessons?

325
00:29:52,070 --> 00:29:53,560
哦，我知道行情的
Oh, l know what's right.

326
00:29:53,670 --> 00:29:58,440
我的朋友和法国人学法语 每小时1 8便士
A lady friend of mine gets French lessons for 18 pence an hour... from a real French gentleman.

327
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:03,880
你不会有脸要我学自己的母语 付同样价钱
You wouldn't have the face t' ask me the same... for teachin' me my own language as you would for French.

328
00:30:03,950 --> 00:30:07,010
因此我只会给一先令 随便你要不要
So, l won't give more than a shillin'. Take it or leave it.

329
00:30:09,450 --> 00:30:12,080
平克林，如果你认为这一先令
Do you know, Pickering, if you think of a shilling...

330
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:16,750
这不是普通一先令 但以这女孩收入的百分比而言
not as a simple shilling, but as a percentage of this girl's income...

331
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:24,100
这相当百万富翁的 60或70英镑
it works out as fully equivalent of... 60 or 70 pounds from a millionaire.

332
00:30:24,940 --> 00:30:28,340
天啊，真多 这是我收入最多的一次
By George, it's enormous. lt's the biggest offer l ever had.

333
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:34,910
60英镑？你在说什么？ 我不能给你60英镑
Sixty pounds? What are you talkin' about? Where would l get 60 pounds? l never offered you 60 pounds!

334
00:30:34,980 --> 00:30:36,810
我没有60英镑！
But l ain't got 60 pounds!

335
00:30:36,910 --> 00:30:40,870
别哭，傻孩子，坐下 没人会动你的钱
Don't cry, you silly girl. Sit down. Nobody's going to touch your money.

336
00:30:40,980 --> 00:30:43,980
如果你还鬼叫 有人会用扫把打你
Somebody'll touch you with a broomstick if you don't stop sniveling.

337
00:30:44,090 --> 00:30:45,450
坐下！
Sit down!

338
00:30:49,330 --> 00:30:51,890
人家会以为你是我父亲！
Anybody'd think you was my father!

339
00:30:52,030 --> 00:30:55,400
如果我决定要教你 我会比你父亲还严厉两倍
lf l decide to teach you, l'll be worse than two fathers to you.

340
00:30:56,430 --> 00:30:57,420
拿去
Here.

341
00:30:57,730 --> 00:30:58,760
这干什么？
What's this for?

342
00:30:58,870 --> 00:31:02,530
擦眼泪 将脸上所有的泪水擦干净
To wipe your eyes. To wipe any part of your face that feels moist.

343
00:31:03,270 --> 00:31:05,470
记住这是手帕那是袖子
Remember, that's your handkerchief and that's your sleeve.

344
00:31:05,580 --> 00:31:09,140
如果你想当专柜小姐 就别弄混了
Don't confuse the one with the other if you want to become a lady in a shop.

345
00:31:09,250 --> 00:31:13,240
跟她说这个没用，席根斯先生 她不明白的
lt's no use to talk to her like that, Mr. Higgins. She doesn't understand you.

346
00:31:13,380 --> 00:31:16,610
把手帕给我 他是给我又不是给你
'Ere! Give the 'ankerchief to me. He give it to me, not to you!

347
00:31:17,150 --> 00:31:19,210
席根斯，我很感兴趣
Higgins, l'm interested.

348
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:23,590
你说过的可以训练她 像女公爵般出席大使舞会
What about your boast... that you could pass her off as a duchess at the Embassy Ball?

349
00:31:23,660 --> 00:31:26,290
如果你办到了 我会说你是世上最伟大的老师
l'll say you're the greatest teacher alive if you do that.

350
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:30,630
我赌所有的实验费用 你办不到的
l'll bet you all the expenses of the experiment that you can't do it.

351
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:32,630
我会付学费
l'll even pay for the lessons.

352
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:35,470
你人真好，谢谢，长官
Aw, you're real good. Thank ye, Capt'n.

353
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,870
这真是无法抗拒
lt's almost irresistible.

354
00:31:41,510 --> 00:31:45,470
她低俗的如此有趣 真是脏死了
She's so deliciously low. So horribly dirty.

355
00:31:45,580 --> 00:31:49,110
我很干净 我洗了脸洗了手才来的
l ain't dirty! l washed my face an' hands before l come, l did.

356
00:31:49,190 --> 00:31:53,140
我接受 我会让她彻底的改头换面
l'll take it. l'll make a duchess of this draggle-tailed guttersnipe.

357
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:57,050
我们从现在开始，皮尔斯太太 带她下去把她弄干净
We'll start today. This moment. Take her away, Mrs. Pearce, and clean her.

358
00:31:57,160 --> 00:32:00,560
如果洗不干净用砂纸 厨房有炉火吗？
Sandpaper, if it won't come off any other way. ls there a fire in the kitchen?

359
00:32:00,660 --> 00:32:03,690
把她衣服烧了 叫人买些新衣来
Take all her clothes off and burn them and order some new ones.

360
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:06,500
先用纸把她包起来 直到买回来为止
Just wrap her in brown paper till they come.

361
00:32:06,940 --> 00:32:12,070
你真不绅士，竟说这种话 我是个好女孩
You're no gentleman, you're not, to talk o' such things. l'm a good girl, l am.

362
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:14,970
我知道你是那种人，真的
And l know what the likes of you are, l do.

363
00:32:15,650 --> 00:32:18,940
我们不要你假正经，年轻女孩
We want none of your slum prudery here, young woman.

364
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:21,350
你是学变成一位女公爵
You've got to learn to behave like a duchess.

365
00:32:21,450 --> 00:32:24,890
带她走，皮尔斯太太 如果她找麻烦就打她
Take 'er away, Mrs. Pearce, an' if she gives you any trouble wallop 'er.

366
00:32:24,990 --> 00:32:26,790
我会报警的
l'll call the police, l will.

367
00:32:26,890 --> 00:32:28,480
但我没有地方可以安置她
l've got no place to put her.

368
00:32:28,590 --> 00:32:30,290
把她放到垃圾桶里
Well, put her in the dustbin.

369
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:33,490
拜托，席根斯，讲理一点
Come, Higgins, be reasonable.

370
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:38,860
你得讲理一点，席根斯先生 你不能这样践踏人！
You must be reasonable, Mr. Higgins, really you must. You can't walk over everybody like this.

371
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:45,170
我？践踏别人？
l? Walk over everybody?

372
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:49,410
亲爱的皮尔斯太太，平克林 我并无意要践踏别人
My dear Mrs. Pearce, my dear Pickering, l had no intention of walking over anyone.

373
00:32:49,510 --> 00:32:52,570
我只是建议 我们要对这女孩仁慈点
l merely suggested we should be kind to this poor girl.

374
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:57,340
我没说清楚 那是我不想伤害她小小的心灵
l didn't express myself clearly because l didn't wish to hurt her delicacy...

375
00:32:57,790 --> 00:32:58,880
或是你们的
or yours.

376
00:32:58,990 --> 00:33:02,120
但是，先生 你不能对一个女孩这样
But, sir, you can't take a girl up like that...

377
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:04,820
好像是你从沙滩边 检回来的石头
as if you were picking up a pebble on the beach.

378
00:33:04,930 --> 00:33:06,190
为何不能？
Why not?

379
00:33:06,300 --> 00:33:09,060
为何不能？你对她一无所知
Why not? But you don't know anything about her.

380
00:33:09,170 --> 00:33:12,070
她的父母是谁？也许她结过婚
What about her parents? She may be married.

381
00:33:12,170 --> 00:33:13,530
格恩！
Garn!

382
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:16,930
这是这女孩常说的“格恩” ！
There. As the girl very properly says, garn!

383
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:19,400
谁会和我结婚？
Who'd marry me?

384
00:33:21,710 --> 00:33:23,510
天啊，伊莱莎...
By George, Eliza...

385
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:31,740
在我造就你之前 外面的人宁愿自杀也要避开你
the streets will be strewn with the bodies of men... shooting themselves for your sake before l've done with you.

386
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:35,260
我要走了
'Ere. l'm goin'.

387
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:39,090
他是个白痴 我不要这个疯子教我
He's off his chump, he is. l don't want no balmies teachin' me.

388
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:42,320
疯子？好，皮尔斯太太 不必为她买新衣了
Mad, am l? All right, Mrs. Pearce, don't order those new clothes.

389
00:33:42,430 --> 00:33:44,630
把她赶出去！ 席根斯先生，我不同意这样
-Throw her out. -Stop, Mr. Higgins! l won't allow it.

390
00:33:44,730 --> 00:33:46,200
回到你父母身边去，女孩
Go home to your parents, girl.

391
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:48,170
我没有父母
l ain't got no parents.

392
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:50,260
她没有父母，干嘛大惊小怪？
She ain't got no parents. What's the fuss about?

393
00:33:50,370 --> 00:33:53,670
没人要她，她对别人没用 但对我有用，带她上楼去
Nobody wants her. She's no use to anybody but me. Take her upstairs!

394
00:33:53,780 --> 00:33:56,250
她会变得如何？ 你要付钱给她吗？
What's to become of her? ls she to be paid anything?

395
00:33:56,350 --> 00:33:58,310
哦，先生，明智一点
Oh, do be sensible, sir.

396
00:33:58,420 --> 00:34:02,180
她要钱干嘛？她衣食充足 如果给她钱她会去喝酒的
What would she do with money? She'll have food and clothes. She'll only drink if you give her money.

397
00:34:02,250 --> 00:34:06,780
你真粗鲁，这是谎言 我从不喝酒的
You are a brute! lt's a lie! Nobody ever saw the sign o' liquor on me.

398
00:34:06,890 --> 00:34:09,950
先生，你是绅士 别让他如此藐视我！
Sir, you're a gentleman. Don't let 'im speak to me like that!

399
00:34:10,060 --> 00:34:12,990
你感觉到了吗？ 席根斯，她有感情的
Does it occur to you, Higgins, the girl has some feelings?

400
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:16,200
不，我不认为 我们不必担心她的感受
No, l don't think so. No feelings we need worry about.

401
00:34:16,670 --> 00:34:17,720
你有吗，伊莱莎？
Well, have you, Eliza?

402
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:20,170
我和别人一样有情感
l got me feelings same as anyone else.

403
00:34:20,270 --> 00:34:23,760
席根斯先生 我想知道这女孩在这里的条件
Mr. Higgins, l must know on what terms the girl is to be here.

404
00:34:23,870 --> 00:34:26,030
当你教完之后，她该怎么办？
What's to become of her when you've finished your teaching?

405
00:34:26,140 --> 00:34:27,970
你必须先想好，先生？
You must look ahead a little, sir.

406
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:31,310
如果她还生活在贫民窟 会是怎么样，皮尔斯太太？
What's to become of her if we leave her in the gutter, Mrs. Pearce?

407
00:34:31,410 --> 00:34:33,710
那是她的自己事，不是你的事 席根斯先生
That's her own business, not yours, Mr. Higgins.

408
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:35,440
我教完了她就回贫民窟
When l'm done we'll throw her back.

409
00:34:35,550 --> 00:34:38,540
那又是为她的自己事 就没有关系了
Then it'll be her own business again. That'll be all right, won't it?

410
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,520
你真的是无情无义！
You've no feelin' 'eart in ya !

411
00:34:41,720 --> 00:34:44,120
你除了自己之外 其他的都不关心
You don't care for nothin' but yourself.

412
00:34:44,430 --> 00:34:48,760
我受够了，我真的要走了 你该为自己感到羞耻
l've 'ad enough of this. l'm goin', l am ! You ought to be ashamed of yourself!

413
00:34:48,830 --> 00:34:50,660
吃点巧克力，伊莱莎
Have some chocolates, Eliza.

414
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:59,200
我怎么知道这里面有什么？
'Ow do l know what might be in 'em?

415
00:34:59,310 --> 00:35:02,210
我听说很多女孩都因此受骗
l've 'eard of girls bein' drugged by the likes o' you.

416
00:35:02,810 --> 00:35:04,180
我保证
Pledge of good faith.

417
00:35:05,050 --> 00:35:06,610
我吃一半
l'll take one half.

418
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:08,970
你吃另一半
And you take the other.

419
00:35:12,660 --> 00:35:15,560
你每天都会有 好几个盒巧克力可以吃
You'll have boxes of them, barrels of them every day.

420
00:35:16,130 --> 00:35:17,520
你可以三餐都吃
You'll live on them, eh?

421
00:35:19,500 --> 00:35:22,830
我不会这样吃 除非我需要才会吃它
l wouldn't 've ate it, only l'm too laidylike to take it out o' me mouth.

422
00:35:22,930 --> 00:35:29,240
想想看，伊莱莎 巧克力和车子还有黄金，钻石
Think of it, Eliza. Think of chocolates, and taxis... and gold and diamonds.

423
00:35:30,510 --> 00:35:34,240
我不要黄金和钻石 我是个好女孩
l don't want no gold and no diamonds. l'm a good girl, l am.

424
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:38,100
席根斯，我必须要说 皮尔斯太太说的非常对
Higgins, l really must interfere. Mrs. Pearce is quite right.

425
00:35:38,210 --> 00:35:41,120
如果这女孩 要参与你的六个月实验
lf this girl's going to put herself in your hands for six months...

426
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:45,280
她一定要完全了解她在作什么
for an experiment in teaching, she must understand thoroughly what she's doing.

427
00:35:48,530 --> 00:35:56,190
伊莱莎，你今后这六个月 住在这学习像淑女般地说话
You are to stay here for the next six months... learning how to speak beautifully like a lady in a florist shop.

428
00:35:57,200 --> 00:36:00,900
如果你很乖，照我的话做 你会有很舒适的卧房可以睡
lf you're good and do what you're told, you shall sleep in a proper bedroom...

429
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:05,300
有很多东西吃 有钱买巧克力还车子可以坐
have lots to eat, money to buy chocolates and take rides in taxis.

430
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:11,780
但是如果你顽皮，懒惰 你在厨房跟蟑螂睡
But if you are naughty and idle... you shall sleep in the kitchen amongst the black beetles...

431
00:36:11,850 --> 00:36:14,720
并被皮尔斯太太用扫把打
and be walloped by Mrs. Pearce with a broomstick.

432
00:36:16,220 --> 00:36:23,920
六个月后，你就会坐着马车 穿着漂亮衣服去白金汉宫
At the end of six months, you shall be taken to Buckingham Palace... in a carriage, beautifully dressed.

433
00:36:24,030 --> 00:36:27,020
如果国王发现你不是淑女
lf the King finds out that you are not a lady...

434
00:36:27,130 --> 00:36:31,400
警察会抓你去伦敦塔 把你的头砍掉
the police will take you to the Tower of London where your head will be cut off...

435
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:34,470
用来警告其他傲慢的卖花女
as a warning to other presumptuous flower girls.

436
00:36:35,470 --> 00:36:38,300
但是如果你没被发现 你会有礼物
But if you are not found out you shall have a present of...

437
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:43,240
会有机会成为 从事花店生意的淑女
seven and six to start life with as a lady in a shop.

438
00:36:44,550 --> 00:36:50,540
如果你拒绝 你就是个薄情的讨厌女孩
lf you refuse this offer... you will be the most ungrateful, wicked girl...

439
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:54,580
天使也会为你悲叹！
and the angels will weep for you!

440
00:36:59,660 --> 00:37:01,250
满意了吗，平克林？
Now are you satisfied, Pickering?

441
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:03,200
我不知道你在说些什么
l don't understand what you are talking about.

442
00:37:03,300 --> 00:37:05,730
要我再进一步说明吗 皮尔斯太太？
Could l put it more plainly or fairly, Mrs. Pearce?

443
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:06,730
跟我来，伊莱沙
Come with me.

444
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:09,600
这样就对了，带她去浴室
That's right. Bundle her off to the bathroom.

445
00:37:09,710 --> 00:37:12,000
你很会欺负人！
You're a great bully, you are!

446
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:14,840
只要我不高兴我就走人 我不要让别人打我！
l won't stay here if l don't like it. l won't let nobody wallop me!

447
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:16,280
别顶嘴了，女孩
Don't answer back, girl.

448
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:22,150
早知如此我不该来这里 我是个好女孩 不要打我
l've always been a good girl, l 'ave.

449
00:37:22,250 --> 00:37:25,120
六个月，三个月后 如果她学习得快
ln six months-- ln three, if she has a good ear and a quick tongue...

