只要一点点好运气！
With a little bit o'bloomin'luck!

637
00:50:49,930 --> 00:50:51,050
邮件，先生
The mail, sir.

638
00:50:51,430 --> 00:50:53,760
把帐单付了 然后回拒所有的邀请
Pay the bills and say no to the invitations.

639
00:51:39,340 --> 00:51:41,870
你不能对女孩这样做
You simply cannot go on working the girl this way.

640
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:47,140
要她一直练习 每天从早到晚都在语言练习
Making her say her alphabet over and over... from sunup to sundown, even during meals.

641
00:51:47,250 --> 00:51:49,810
你会累坏，何时可以停下来？
You'll exhaust yourself. When will it stop?

642
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:53,120
等她发音正确为止 还有事吗，皮尔斯太太？
When she does it properly, of course. ls that all, Mrs. Pearce?

643
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:57,090
这封信是美国百万富翁 以斯拉寄来的
There's another letter from that American millionaire, Ezra D. Wallingford.

644
00:51:57,190 --> 00:51:59,390
他还是希望你 为道德改革会工作
He still wants you for his Moral Reform League.

645
00:51:59,500 --> 00:52:00,550
把它丢了
Throw it away.

646
00:52:00,660 --> 00:52:04,120
这是第三封了 至少你该回封信吧
lt's the third letter he's written you, sir. You should at least answer it.

647
00:52:04,230 --> 00:52:06,860
好，放在书桌上，皮尔斯太太 我会试着回信
All right, leave it on the desk, Mrs. Pearce. l'll try an' get to it.

648
00:52:10,340 --> 00:52:14,370
如果可以，先生 楼下有清洁工亚尔杜立特尔
lf you please, sir. There's a dustman downstairs, Alfred P. Doolittle...

649
00:52:14,510 --> 00:52:17,450
想要见你 他说他的女儿在这里
who wants to see you. He says you have his daughter here.

650
00:52:17,580 --> 00:52:18,710
去！我说！
Phew! l say!

651
00:52:20,050 --> 00:52:21,610
叫那个无赖上来，亚当
Well, send the blackguard up.

652
00:52:22,150 --> 00:52:24,050
他可能不是无赖，席根斯
He may not be a blackguard, Higgins.

653
00:52:24,190 --> 00:52:26,810
哦，他毫无疑问地是无赖 平克林
Oh, nonsense. O' course he's a blackguard, Pickering.

654
00:52:26,920 --> 00:52:29,290
我怕他是来找麻烦的
l'm afraid we'll have some trouble with him.

655
00:52:29,390 --> 00:52:33,230
不，不会的 是我找他麻烦不是他找我
No, l think not. Any trouble to be had, he'll have it with me. Not l with him.

656
00:52:37,130 --> 00:52:38,570
这位是杜立特尔，先生
Doolittle, sir.

657
00:52:44,970 --> 00:52:47,170
席根斯教授？ 在这里！
-Professor 'lggins? -Here!

658
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:49,270
在哪里？
Where?

659
00:52:49,850 --> 00:52:51,710
早安，先生
Good morning, Governor.

660
00:52:52,110 --> 00:52:55,210
我是为一件重要的事而来 先生
l come about a very serious matter, Governor.

661
00:52:58,650 --> 00:53:00,710
在宏士罗洛长大的
Brought up in Houndslow.

662
00:53:01,390 --> 00:53:03,220
我想你母亲是威尔斯人
Mother Welsh, l should think.

663
00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:05,880
你要干什么？杜立特尔先生
What is it you want, Doolittle?

664
00:53:05,990 --> 00:53:08,390
我要我女儿，懂吗？
l want my daughter, that's what l want. See?

665
00:53:08,630 --> 00:53:11,120
你当然是要你女儿 你是她父亲，对吧？
Of course you do. You're her father, aren't you?

666
00:53:11,230 --> 00:53:13,830
我很高兴你对家人还有感情
l'm glad to see you have a spark of family feeling left.

667
00:53:13,940 --> 00:53:16,560
她在里面，可以马上带她走
She's in there. Yes, take her away at once.

668
00:53:16,740 --> 00:53:17,760
什么？
What?

669
00:53:18,310 --> 00:53:21,970
把她带走，我才不替你养女儿
Take her away. Do you think l am going to keep your daughter for you?

670
00:53:22,410 --> 00:53:25,140
这样合理吗？
Now, is this reasonable, Governor?

671
00:53:25,310 --> 00:53:28,340
这样占一个人便宜公平吗？
ls it fairity to take advantage of a man like that?

672
00:53:28,520 --> 00:53:31,780
这女孩属于我，你却得到她 我该怎么办？
The girl belongs to me. You got 'er. Where do l come in?

673
00:53:32,250 --> 00:53:35,920
你竟然敢来这里企图勒索我！
How dare you come here and attempt to blackmail me!

674
00:53:36,490 --> 00:53:38,080
你故意送她到这里来！
You sent her here on purpose!

675
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:41,890
别这样刁难人，先生
Don't take a man up like that, Governor.

676
00:53:42,030 --> 00:53:46,700
警察应该逮捕你 这是个勒索计划
The police shall take you up. This is a plan... a plot to extort money by threats.

677
00:53:46,770 --> 00:53:48,430
我应该打电话报警
l shall telephone the police.

678
00:53:48,840 --> 00:53:51,830
我有向你要钱了吗？
Have l asked you for a brass farthin'?

679
00:53:52,340 --> 00:53:55,610
我们可以问这位先生 我提到了钱吗？
l leave it to this gentleman 'ere. Have l said a word about money?

680
00:53:56,010 --> 00:53:57,980
那你来干什么？
Well, what else did you come for?

681
00:54:00,080 --> 00:54:04,350
我能干什么 有点人情味嘛，先生
What would a bloke come for? Be 'uman, Governor.

682
00:54:09,460 --> 00:54:12,430
亚尔，你故意把她送来这里
Alfred, you sent her here on purpose.

683
00:54:12,530 --> 00:54:14,190
拜托，先生，我从未这样做
So help me, Governor, l never did.

684
00:54:14,300 --> 00:54:15,490
那你怎么知道她在这里？
Then how did you know she was here?

685
00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:18,530
我正要告诉你，先生 如果你让我说的话
l'd tell you, Governor, if you'd only let me get a word in.

686
00:54:18,770 --> 00:54:23,800
我会告诉你，我要告诉你 我等着要告诉你！
l'm willing to tell ya. l'm wanting to tell ya. l'm waiting to tell ya !

687
00:54:25,370 --> 00:54:29,240
平克林 这就是特定的自然修辞法
You know, Pickering, this chap's got a certain natural gift of rhetoric.

688
00:54:29,650 --> 00:54:32,550
注意他说话的原始韵律
Observe the rhythm of his native woodnotes wild.

689
00:54:32,810 --> 00:54:36,650
“我会告诉你，我要告诉你 我等着要告诉你”
''l'm willing to tell you. l'm wanting to tell you. l'm waiting to tell you.''

690
00:54:36,850 --> 00:54:39,010
他说的是威尔斯腔调
That's the Welsh strain in 'im.

691
00:54:39,390 --> 00:54:41,880
如果不是你叫伊莱莎来 你怎么知道她在这里？
How did you know Eliza was here if you didn't send 'er?

692
00:54:41,990 --> 00:54:45,450
她叫人回来拿她的行李 而我碰巧听到了
Well, she sent back for her luggage and l got to 'ear about it.

693
00:54:45,560 --> 00:54:48,290
她说她不要衣服了
She said she didn't want no clothes.

694
00:54:48,900 --> 00:54:53,730
我会怎么想？我问你 我是父亲，我该怎么想？
What was l to think from that, Governor? l ask you, as a parent, what was l to think?

695
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:57,870
所以你是来这里救她的？
So you came here to rescue her from worse than death, eh?

696
00:54:58,110 --> 00:55:00,540
是的，先生，没错 是
-Yes, sir, Governor. That's right. -Yes.

697
00:55:01,010 --> 00:55:02,410
皮尔斯太太！
Mrs. Pearce!

698
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:03,870
皮尔斯太太
Mrs. Pearce!

699
00:55:03,980 --> 00:55:07,280
伊莱沙的父亲来带她了 把她交给他，好吗？
Eliza's father has come to take her away. Give her to him, will you?

700
00:55:07,380 --> 00:55:10,780
等一下，先生，等一下
Now wait a minute, Governor. Wait a minute.

701
00:55:11,750 --> 00:55:14,420
你和我都是这世上的男人吧 不是吗？
You and me is men o' the world, ain't we?

702
00:55:14,920 --> 00:55:18,980
这世上的男人吧，是吗？ 皮尔太太你最好快走
Men of the world, are we? Perhaps you'd better go, Mrs. Pearce.

703
00:55:19,090 --> 00:55:20,580
我也是这么想，先生！
l think so indeed, sir!

704
00:55:21,230 --> 00:55:25,870
先生，我对你很有好感...
Here, Governor. l've took a sort of a fancy to you and...

705
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:32,540
如果你要这个女孩 我就不带她走了...
if you want the girl, l ain't so set on 'avin' her back home again...

706
00:55:32,640 --> 00:55:35,580
但是我有些事情要解决
but what l might be open to is an arrangement.

707
00:55:35,980 --> 00:55:38,410
我所要求的是父亲的权利
All l ask is my rights as a father.

708
00:55:38,510 --> 00:55:42,140
你一定不希望我 毫无代价地就让她离开我
You're the last man alive to expect me to let her go for nothing.

709
00:55:42,480 --> 00:55:45,720
我看得出你是很正直的人 先生
l can see you're o' the straight sort, Governor.

710
00:55:45,820 --> 00:55:47,020
所以...
So...

711
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:50,920
5英镑对你有无差吧 伊莱莎对我也无差
what's a five pound note to you? An' what's Eliza to me?

712
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,220
我想你应该知道，杜立特尔...
l think you ought to know, Doolittle...

713
00:55:53,330 --> 00:55:56,350
席根斯先生的用意是很崇高的
that Mr. Higgins' intentions are entirely honorable.

714
00:55:56,900 --> 00:56:00,730
当然，先生 否则我要50英镑
Of course they are, Governor. lf l thought they wasn't, l'd ask 50.

715
00:56:01,240 --> 00:56:04,070
你是说你用50英镑卖女儿？
Do you mean to say you'd sell your daughter for 50 pounds?

716
00:56:04,170 --> 00:56:05,900
你没道德良心吗？
Have you no morals, man?

717
00:56:08,910 --> 00:56:12,740
如果你跟我一样穷 你也会没有的，先生
No, l can't afford 'em, Governor. Neither could you if you was as poor as me.

718
00:56:13,080 --> 00:56:15,280
我没有恶意，但...
Not that l mean any 'arm, mind ya, but...

719
00:56:15,380 --> 00:56:18,940
如果伊莱沙可以 为何我不可以呢？
if Eliza is gonna have a bit out o' this, why not me, too?

720
00:56:20,160 --> 00:56:21,250
为何？
Why not?

721
00:56:21,360 --> 00:56:22,790
那么...
Well, look....

722
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:26,820
用我的观点来看 我算什么了？
Look at it my way. What am l?

723
00:56:27,700 --> 00:56:31,760
我问你我算什么？ 我是毫无价值的穷人，就是我
l ask ya, what am l? l'm one o' the undeserving poor, that's what l am.

724
00:56:31,870 --> 00:56:33,860
想想看这对人的意义
Now think what that means to a man.

725
00:56:33,970 --> 00:56:37,670
意思是他一生都在对抗 中等阶级的道德观
lt means he's up against middle-class morality for all the time.

726
00:56:38,270 --> 00:56:42,000
如果任何情况发生了 永远都会有一样结果
lf there's anything goin' an' l puts in for a bit of it, it's always the same story:

727
00:56:42,110 --> 00:56:44,340
你没有价值，所以不能给你
''You're undeservin', so you can't have it.''

728
00:56:45,110 --> 00:56:49,070
但我需要的钱 和寡妇需要的是一样
But my needs is as great as the most deservin' widows that ever got money...

729
00:56:49,180 --> 00:56:53,380
她是从过世的丈夫身份 得来的救济金
out of six different charities in one week for the death o' the same 'usband.

730
00:56:53,790 --> 00:56:57,280
我需要的不比别人少 我需要的更多
l don't need less than a deservin' man, l need more.

731
00:56:57,760 --> 00:57:00,750
我吃的不少，并且爱喝酒...
l don't eat less 'earty than he does and l drink...

732
00:57:01,530 --> 00:57:02,660
喝很多
a lot more.

733
00:57:03,100 --> 00:57:04,790
我就跟你直话直说
l'm playin' straight with you.

734
00:57:05,170 --> 00:57:08,900
我不打算假装我应得 不，我是不应该这样
l ain't pretendin' to be deservin'. No, l'm undeservin'...

735
00:57:09,400 --> 00:57:13,140
而我就是没有价值 我喜欢，这是事实
and l mean to go on bein' undeservin'. l like it an' that's the truth.

736
00:57:13,510 --> 00:57:17,100
但是你会占人便宜吗...
But will you take advantage of a man's nature...

737
00:57:17,580 --> 00:57:23,350
我好不容易把她扶养长大 为她做了一切...
do him out of the price of his own daughter, what he's brought up... fed and clothed by the sweat of his brow...

738
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:28,980
直到现在 她大到可以吸引你们两位
till she's growed big enough to be interestin' to you two gentlemen?

739
00:57:30,930 --> 00:57:34,230
5英镑不合理吗，看你们了？
ls five pounds unreasonable, l put it to you?

740
00:57:34,630 --> 00:57:36,260
我把问题交给你
And l leave it to you.

741
00:57:39,070 --> 00:57:42,660
平克林 如果我们若训练他三个月...
You know, Pickering, if we took this man in hand for three months...

742
00:57:42,770 --> 00:57:46,640
他就能在内阁或教区间 选个职位
he could choose between a seat in the Cabinet and a popular pulpit in Wales.

743
00:57:47,580 --> 00:57:51,310
我们最好给他5英镑 他会滥用这些钱
-We'd better give 'im a fiver. -He'll make bad use of it, l'm afraid.

744
00:57:51,410 --> 00:57:53,440
不会的，先生，相信我不会
Not me, Governor, so 'elp me l won't.

745
00:57:53,550 --> 00:57:56,040
这只是我和内人喝酒的钱...
Just one good spree for meself an' the missus...

746
00:57:56,150 --> 00:57:59,090
带给自己欢乐 和别人工作的机会
givin' pleasure to ourselves and employment to others.

747
00:57:59,450 --> 00:58:03,950
你该满意钱不会被浪费 这是最好的选择
An' satisfaction to you to know it ain't been throwed away. You couldn't spend it better.

748
00:58:04,030 --> 00:58:06,320
哦，真难拒绝 给他1 0英镑好了
Oh, this is irresistible. Let's give 'im ten.

749
00:58:06,430 --> 00:58:07,330
不行
No

750
00:58:07,430 --> 00:58:09,360
内人不知道要如何花1 0英镑 先生
The missus wouldn't have the 'eart to spend ten, Governor.

751
00:58:09,460 --> 00:58:11,130
1 0英镑太多了
Ten pounds is a lot o' money.

752
00:58:11,230 --> 00:58:14,790
那会让人审慎考虑 不再快乐了
Makes a man feel prudent-like, and then goodbye to 'appiness.

753
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:19,040
你只要给我5英镑，不多不少
No, you just give me what l ask, Governor. Not a penny less, not a penny more.

754
00:58:19,340 --> 00:58:22,640
我很想插手管这件不道德的事 杜立特尔
l rather draw the line at encouraging this sort of immorality, Doolittle.

755
00:58:22,740 --> 00:58:24,800
你为何不跟她结婚呢？
Why don't you marry that missus of yours?

756
00:58:24,910 --> 00:58:28,210
毕竟婚姻不可怕 何况你和伊莱沙母亲结过婚
After all, marriage isn't so frightening. You married Eliza's mother.

757
00:58:28,420 --> 00:58:30,010
谁说的，先生？
Who told you that, Governor?

758
00:58:30,120 --> 00:58:32,950
没人告诉我是 是我自己想到的...
Well, nobody told me. l concluded, naturally....

759
00:58:37,090 --> 00:58:40,220
如果他再说一分钟 我们就没有信心了
lf we listen to this man for another minute we shall have no convictions left.

760
00:58:40,330 --> 00:58:43,230
你说的5英镑 谢谢，先生
-Five pounds, l think you said. -Thank you, Governor.

761
00:58:43,430 --> 00:58:44,800
确定不要1 0英镑？
Are you sure you won't have ten?

762
00:58:44,900 --> 00:58:47,200
不...或许下次好了
No. No, perhaps another time.

763
00:58:49,140 --> 00:58:50,370
对不起，小姐
l beg your pardon, Miss.

764
00:58:50,470 --> 00:58:53,240
我不要再说这些母音了
l won't say those ruddy vowels one more time.

765
00:58:53,340 --> 00:58:54,970
我的天啊，是伊莱莎
Blimey, it's Eliza.

766
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:57,840
我从不知道她弄干净之后 会这么漂亮
Well, l never thought she'd clean up so good-looking.

767
00:58:57,950 --> 00:58:59,940
真是我的光荣，不是吗，先生
She does me credit, don't she, Governor?

768
00:59:00,050 --> 00:59:02,540
等等，你来这里干什么？
Here! What are you doin' here?

