1101
01:26:02,570 --> 01:26:04,730
我好像见过你 我不知道
-l've seen you somewhere before. -l don't know.

1102
01:26:04,830 --> 01:26:07,130
没关系，你最好坐下吧
lt doesn't matter. You better sit down.

1103
01:26:10,870 --> 01:26:12,530
他们到哪里去了？
Where the devil can they be?

1104
01:26:48,110 --> 01:26:49,940
平克林上校 你正好赶上喝茶的时间
Colonel Pickering, you're just in time for tea.

1105
01:26:50,050 --> 01:26:53,310
谢谢，席根斯夫人 容我介绍伊莱莎杜立特尔小姐
Thank you, Mrs. Higgins. May l introduce Miss Eliza Doolittle?

1106
01:26:53,420 --> 01:26:54,750
亲爱的，杜立特尔小姐
My dear, Miss Doolittle.

1107
01:26:54,850 --> 01:26:57,550
你请我来真是太好了
How kind of you to let me come.

1108
01:26:57,650 --> 01:26:58,980
我很高兴你能来
Delighted, my dear.

1109
01:27:00,420 --> 01:27:02,750
巴克辛顿夫人 你好？
-Lady Boxington. -How do you do?

1110
01:27:02,860 --> 01:27:04,190
你好
-How do you do?

1111
01:27:04,290 --> 01:27:06,020
巴克辛顿阁下 你好？
-Lord Boxington. -How do you do?

1112
01:27:06,130 --> 01:27:07,060
你好？
How do you do?

1113
01:27:07,160 --> 01:27:10,060
恩斯福特夫人，杜立特尔小姐 你好？
-Mrs. Eynsford-Hill, Miss Doolittle. -How do you do?

1114
01:27:10,170 --> 01:27:11,790
你好？
How do you do?

1115
01:27:11,900 --> 01:27:13,770
还有佛雷狄恩斯福特希尔
And Freddy Eynsford-Hill.

1116
01:27:14,940 --> 01:27:16,500
你好？
How do you do?

1117
01:27:18,840 --> 01:27:20,400
你好？
How do you do?

1118
01:27:21,180 --> 01:27:22,270
杜立特尔小姐
Miss Doolittle.

1119
01:27:22,710 --> 01:27:25,870
午安，席根斯教授
Good afternoon, Professor Higgins.

1120
01:27:35,090 --> 01:27:40,120
第一场赛马很刺激 杜立特尔小姐，可惜你错过了
The first race was very exciting, Miss Doolittle. l'm so sorry that you missed it.

1121
01:27:40,360 --> 01:27:42,090
你认为会下雨吗？
Will it rain, do you think?

1122
01:27:42,460 --> 01:27:46,700
西班牙的雨大多数落在平原上
The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain.

1123
01:27:51,710 --> 01:27:57,200
但是在哈特福特，赫里福 和汉普郡，没有发生飓风
But in Hartford, Hereford and Hampshire, hurricanes hardly ever happen.

1124
01:27:57,580 --> 01:27:59,010
这真的很好笑
How awfully funny.

1125
01:27:59,220 --> 01:28:02,650
有何不对，年轻人？ 我想我说对了
What is wrong with that, young man? l bet l got it right.

1126
01:28:02,950 --> 01:28:03,880
真妙
Smashing.

1127
01:28:04,320 --> 01:28:06,790
难道天气不会突然变冷吗？
Has it suddenly turned chilly?

1128
01:28:07,290 --> 01:28:10,820
我希望不会染上非季节性感冒
l do hope we won't have any unseasonable cold spells.

1129
01:28:10,930 --> 01:28:12,890
否则会引起流行性感冒
They bring on so much influenza.

1130
01:28:13,000 --> 01:28:15,730
我的家人会很容易染上
And the whole of our family is susceptible to it.

1131
01:28:15,830 --> 01:28:20,630
他们是说我姑姑死于感冒
My aunt died of influenza, so they said.

1132
01:28:20,740 --> 01:28:24,640
但我相信是他们解决了她
But it's my belief they done the old woman in.

1133
01:28:25,740 --> 01:28:27,110
解决了她？
Done her in?

1134
01:28:27,640 --> 01:28:29,340
是的，上帝爱你
Yes, Lord love you.

1135
01:28:29,610 --> 01:28:32,010
她为什么会死于感冒...
Why should she die of influenza...

1136
01:28:32,110 --> 01:28:35,610
一年前她得了白喉但痊愈了
when she come through diphtheria right enough the year before.

1137
01:28:36,150 --> 01:28:38,520
她为此非常担忧
Fairly blue with it she was.

1138
01:28:39,050 --> 01:28:40,890
他们都以为她死了
They all thought she was dead.

1139
01:28:40,990 --> 01:28:45,430
但我父亲用汤匙装琴酒给她喝
But my father, he kept ladling gin down her throat.

1140
01:28:50,100 --> 01:28:54,800
直到她咬断汤匙的把手
Then she come to so sudden she bit the bowl off the spoon.

1141
01:28:55,770 --> 01:28:57,240
天啊！
Dear me!

1142
01:28:58,410 --> 01:29:03,670
为何如此强壮的女人 会死于感冒？
Now what call would a woman with that strength in her... have to die of influenza?

1143
01:29:04,650 --> 01:29:09,210
她该给我的新草帽下场呢？
And what become of her new straw hat that should have come to me?

1144
01:29:11,490 --> 01:29:14,250
有人偷走了
Somebody pinched it.

1145
01:29:15,020 --> 01:29:20,720
我要说的是 他们偷走了，解决了她
And what l say is: Them 'as pinched it, done her in.

1146
01:29:21,300 --> 01:29:24,460
解决了她？你是这样说的吗？
Done her in? Done her in, did you say?

1147
01:29:24,630 --> 01:29:26,260
这是什么意思？
Whatever does it mean?

1148
01:29:26,370 --> 01:29:31,500
哦，这是新术语 解决某人的意思是杀了他们
Oh, that's the new small talk. ''To do somebody in'' means to kill them.

1149
01:29:31,670 --> 01:29:35,130
但你不会相信 你姑姑是被杀的吧？
But you surely don't believe your aunt was killed?

1150
01:29:35,240 --> 01:29:36,770
我不会吗？
Do l not?

1151
01:29:36,880 --> 01:29:42,110
他们为了一根针都会杀她 更别说一顶帽子
Them she lived with would have killed her for a hatpin, let alone a hat.

1152
01:29:42,220 --> 01:29:47,680
但你父亲不该拿酒喂她喝
But it can't have been right for your father... to pour spirits down her throat like that.

1153
01:29:47,790 --> 01:29:49,450
这可能会杀了她
lt might have killed her.

1154
01:29:49,560 --> 01:29:53,790
她不会，琴酒对她来说是母乳
Not her. Gin was mother's milk to her.

1155
01:29:53,900 --> 01:29:59,560
而且他自己喝了更多
Besides, he poured so much down his own throat he knew the good of it.

1156
01:29:59,670 --> 01:30:01,330
你是说他喝酒？
Do you mean that he drank?

1157
01:30:01,440 --> 01:30:05,030
喝酒？这积习难改
Drank? My word. Something chronic.

1158
01:30:08,110 --> 01:30:11,570
你笑些什么？
Here, what are you sniggering at?

1159
01:30:11,680 --> 01:30:15,310
那新术语，你说得真好
The new small talk. You do it so awfully well.

1160
01:30:15,420 --> 01:30:19,750
如果我说的很恰当 那你笑个什么劲？
Well, if l was doing it proper, what was you sniggering at?

1161
01:30:19,860 --> 01:30:22,450
我是否说了我不该说的吗？
Have l said anything l oughtn't?

1162
01:30:24,030 --> 01:30:25,720
完全没有
Not at all, my dear.

1163
01:30:25,860 --> 01:30:27,950
那就好
Well, that's a mercy anyhow.

1164
01:30:29,930 --> 01:30:35,900
我不知道是否可以赶上 下一场下注但是走吧，亲爱的
l don't know if there's enough time before the next race to place a bet... but come, my dear.

1165
01:30:36,670 --> 01:30:40,130
我下注七号 我很高兴能送给你
l have a bet on number seven. l should be so happy if you would take it.

1166
01:30:40,240 --> 01:30:42,340
你会更喜欢这场赛马的
You'll enjoy the race ever so much more.

1167
01:30:42,440 --> 01:30:44,040
你人真好
That's very kind of you.

1168
01:30:44,150 --> 01:30:45,270
它的名字叫多佛
His name is Dover.

1169
01:30:45,380 --> 01:30:46,750
走吧，伊莱莎
Come along, Eliza.

1170
01:30:50,290 --> 01:30:54,020
它们又来了，准备要起跑
There they are again Lining up to run

1171
01:30:54,390 --> 01:30:58,550
它们屏息以待，准备好了，看
Now they're holding steady They are ready for it, look

1172
01:30:59,530 --> 01:31:01,890
开始了
lt has begun

1173
01:31:07,670 --> 01:31:09,470
加油...多佛
Come on. Come on, Dover.

1174
01:31:10,440 --> 01:31:13,340
加油...多佛
Come on. Come on, Dover!

1175
01:31:13,480 --> 01:31:14,440
加油！
Come on!

1176
01:31:18,880 --> 01:31:23,410
快点，多佛！加速你的玻璃！
Come on, Dover! Move your bloomin' ass!

1177
01:31:29,530 --> 01:31:30,920
哦，亲爱的
Oh, my dear.

1178
01:31:45,870 --> 01:31:49,740
你不是认真的吧，亨利 真的要带她去参加大使舞会
You're not serious, Henry. You don't expect to take her to the Embassy Ball.

1179
01:31:49,850 --> 01:31:51,370
你认为她还没准备好？
Don't you think she's ready for it?

1180
01:31:51,480 --> 01:31:53,850
亲爱的亨利 她比较适合喧闹的场所
Dear Henry, she's ready for a canal barge.

1181
01:31:53,950 --> 01:31:56,180
她的语言或许需要再加强 但是...
Her language may need a little refining, but--

1182
01:31:56,290 --> 01:31:59,880
真的，亨利 你应该了解这是不可能的任务
Really, Henry, if you cannot see how impossible this whole project is...

1183
01:31:59,990 --> 01:32:01,850
你不该为她做愚蠢的事情
then you must be absolutely potty about her.

1184
01:32:01,960 --> 01:32:05,290
我建议你放弃不要折磨你自己 或这可怜的女孩
l advise you to give it up and not put yourself... or this poor girl through any more.

1185
01:32:05,360 --> 01:32:08,090
放弃 这是我最具挑战性的工作
Why, it's the most fascinating venture l've ever undertaken.

1186
01:32:08,200 --> 01:32:11,430
平克林和我日夜不眠地投入 这充实了我们的生命
Pickering and l are at it from morning till night. lt fills our whole lives.

1187
01:32:11,530 --> 01:32:15,330
教导伊莱莎，与伊莱莎对话 听伊莱莎说话，帮伊莱莎穿衣
Teaching Eliza, talking to Eliza, listening to Eliza, dressing Eliza.

1188
01:32:15,440 --> 01:32:16,700
什么？
What

1189
01:32:16,810 --> 01:32:20,300
你像是个小孩在玩洋娃娃游戏
You're a pretty pair of babies playing with your live doll.

1190
01:32:20,410 --> 01:32:21,600
车子来了
Here's the car.

1191
01:33:30,680 --> 01:33:32,040
谢谢
Thank you , sir

1192
01:33:42,930 --> 01:33:43,950
晚安，先生
Good evening, sir.

1193
01:33:44,060 --> 01:33:46,620
晚餐好了没？我饿坏了 立刻就好，先生
-ls dinner ready? l'm famished. -lmmediately, sir.

1194
01:33:46,830 --> 01:33:48,630
晚安，席根斯教授
Good evening, Professor Higgins.

1195
01:34:06,720 --> 01:34:11,310
当她提到她姑姑如何喝东西时
When she mentioned How her aunt bit off the spoon

1196
01:34:11,420 --> 01:34:15,380
她完全把我迷倒了
She completely done me in

1197
01:34:15,490 --> 01:34:19,290
我的心飞到遥远的月球上了
And my heart went on A journey to the moon

1198
01:34:19,390 --> 01:34:24,590
当她提到她父亲和琴酒时
When she told about her father And the gin

1199
01:34:24,700 --> 01:34:29,400
我从未见过如此好笑的行为
And l never saw A more enchanting farce

1200
01:34:29,500 --> 01:34:34,440
当她大声叫 “加速你的...”
Than the moment when she shouted ''Move your bloomin ''--

1201
01:34:34,910 --> 01:34:36,940
什么事？ 杜立特尔小姐在吗？
-Yes, sir? -ls Miss Doolittle in?

1202
01:34:37,050 --> 01:34:38,540
是谁来拜访？
Whom shall l say is calling?

1203
01:34:38,950 --> 01:34:41,970
佛雷狄恩斯福特希尔 如果她不记得我
Freddy Eynsford-Hill. lf she doesn't remember who l am...

1204
01:34:42,350 --> 01:34:45,010
就告诉她 我是看着她笑的年轻人
tell her l'm the chap who was sniggering at her.

1205
01:34:45,390 --> 01:34:46,350
是的
Yes, sir.

1206
01:34:46,460 --> 01:34:48,720
可否将这个给她？ 好
And will you give her these?

1207
01:34:48,820 --> 01:34:52,050
要进来吗？ 他们正在用餐，你在大厅等
Wouldn't you like to come in, sir? They're having dinner, but you may wait in the hall.

1208
01:34:52,130 --> 01:34:55,460
不用了，谢谢 我在外面沉醉一下
No, thank you. l want to drink in the street where she lives.

1209
01:35:04,370 --> 01:35:09,970
我以前常在这条路上漫步
l have often walked Down this street before

1210
01:35:10,080 --> 01:35:15,640
但是脚下的步伐毫无特别
But the pavement always stayed Beneath my feet before

1211
01:35:15,750 --> 01:35:21,250
瞬时间我的思绪飞扬在空中
All at once am l Several stories high

1212
01:35:21,360 --> 01:35:27,160
知道这是你所住的街道
Knowing l'm on the street Where you live

1213
01:35:27,260 --> 01:35:32,890
丁香花不是在市中心吗？
Are there lilac trees ln the heart of town?

1214
01:35:33,000 --> 01:35:38,600
听到云雀在城市中鸣叫？
Can you hear a lark ln any other part of town?

1215
01:35:38,710 --> 01:35:44,300
是否会迷倒所有的住户？
Does enchantment pour Out of every door?

1216
01:35:44,410 --> 01:35:50,650
不，只是因你住在此
No, it's just on the street Where you live

1217
01:35:50,750 --> 01:36:02,290
知道你在附近 那感觉多么强烈
And, oh, the towering feeling Just to know Somehow you are near

1218
01:36:02,400 --> 01:36:07,270
无法抗拒的情感
The overpowering feeling

1219
01:36:07,370 --> 01:36:13,500
因为你随时都会出现
That any second You may suddenly appear

1220
01:36:13,610 --> 01:36:19,340
我不在乎别人的注视
People stop and stare They don't bother me

1221
01:36:19,450 --> 01:36:25,150
我只希望能够在此等你
For there's nowhere else on Earth That l would rather be

1222
01:36:25,250 --> 01:36:33,060
让时光飞逝，我不在乎
Let the time go by l won't care if l

1223
01:36:33,160 --> 01:36:40,160
我只要在你住的街道上等你
Can be here on the street Where you live

1224
01:36:41,040 --> 01:36:42,500
先生
Sir

1225
01:36:45,110 --> 01:36:47,040
非常抱歉，先生
l'm terribly sorry, sir.

1226
01:36:47,180 --> 01:36:50,270
杜立特尔小姐说 她不再见到任何人了
Miss Doolittle says she doesn't want to see anyone ever again.

1227
01:36:50,380 --> 01:36:52,040
为何？她是如此惊艳动人
But why? She was unbelievable.

1228
01:36:52,150 --> 01:36:55,310
我知道了，先生 还有什么话要转告？
So l've been told, sir. ls there any further message?

1229
01:36:55,620 --> 01:36:57,780
有，告诉她我会等的
Tell her that l'll wait.

1230
01:36:57,850 --> 01:37:00,250
哦，那有可能要好几天 甚至一个星期
Oh, but it might be days, sir, even weeks.

1231
01:37:00,360 --> 01:37:02,790
你看不出来吗？ 我在这里很快乐
But don't you see? l'll be happier here.

1232
01:37:11,970 --> 01:37:17,670
我不在乎别人的注视
People stop and stare They don't bother me

1233
01:37:17,770 --> 01:37:23,640
我只希望能在此等你
For there's nowhere else on Earth That l would rather be

1234
01:37:23,750 --> 01:37:32,380
让时光飞逝，我不在乎
Let the time go by l won't care if l

1235
01:37:32,490 --> 01:37:43,230
我只要在你住的街道上等你
Can be here on the street Where you live

1236
01:37:47,300 --> 01:37:50,400
席根斯，是真的 如此下去是很不人道的行为
lt really is, Higgins. lt's inhuman to continue.

1237
01:37:50,510 --> 01:37:53,180
你知道这六周内 你要她做到什么吗？
Do you realize what you've got to try and teach this poor girl in six weeks?

1238
01:37:53,180 --> 01:37:56,040
你要教她走路，说话，穿着 各种阶级的应对礼貌
You've got to teach her to walk, talk, address a duke, a lord...

1239
01:37:56,040 --> 01:37:59,180
根本就是不可能的事
a bishop, an ambassador. lt's absolutely impossible.

1240
01:37:59,280 --> 01:38:02,550
席根斯 我想要取消这次的打赌
Higgins, l'm trying to tell you that l want to call off the bet.

1241
01:38:02,650 --> 01:38:04,880
我和你一样是很顽固的人
l know you're a stubborn man, but so am l.

1242
01:38:04,990 --> 01:38:06,890
实验结束了
This experiment is over.

1243
01:38:06,990 --> 01:38:12,980
连国王的命令也无法改变我意 失陪！
And nothing short of an order from the King could force me to recant.

1244
01:38:13,330 --> 01:38:15,590
明白吗？ 席根斯，实验已结束了
You understand, Higgins? lt's over.

1245
01:38:15,700 --> 01:38:20,230
席根斯，如果今晚 在大使馆发生任何差错
Higgins, if there's any mishap at the Embassy tonight...

1246
01:38:20,340 --> 01:38:22,930
如果杜立特尔小姐 遭受任何侮辱
if Miss Doolittle suffers any embarrassment whatever...

1247
01:38:23,040 --> 01:38:24,270
都将是你个人的责任
it'll be on your head alone.

1248
01:38:24,370 --> 01:38:25,600
伊莱莎能办到的
Eliza can do anything.

1249
01:38:25,710 --> 01:38:27,270
假如她被发现了呢？ 记得赛马场上的事情吗？
Suppose she's discovered? Remember Ascot.

1250
01:38:27,380 --> 01:38:29,240
如果她忘了舞步 或是碰出几句粗话
Suppose she makes another ghastly mistake?

1251
01:38:29,340 --> 01:38:32,140
舞会里没有马的，平克林
There'll be no horses at the ball, Pickering.

1252
01:38:34,280 --> 01:38:36,550
想到了就头大
Think of how agonizing it would be.

1253
01:38:36,650 --> 01:38:39,280
万一今晚发生差错 不知道该如何是好
lf anything happened tonight, l don't know what l'd do.

1254
01:38:39,390 --> 01:38:40,950
你还是可以回部队去
You could always rejoin your regiment.

1255
01:38:41,060 --> 01:38:42,890
没时间开玩笑了，席根斯
This is no time for flippancy, Higgins.

1256
01:38:42,990 --> 01:38:47,220
在过去六周里 已超过那女孩所能承受的礼仪
The way you've driven her the last six weeks... has exceeded all bounds of common decency.

1257
01:38:47,300 --> 01:38:50,260
拜托，别在那里踱步 可否坐下来？
For God's sake, stop pacing up and down. Can't you settle somewhere?

1258
01:38:50,370 --> 01:38:52,300
喝点酒，可以让你不会紧张
Have some port. lt'll quieten your nerves.

1259
01:38:52,400 --> 01:38:53,890
我并不紧张
l'm not nervous.

1260
01:38:55,370 --> 01:38:57,300
酒在哪里？ 在钢琴上面
-Where is it? -On the piano.

1261
01:38:59,270 --> 01:39:00,260
车子已经来了
The car's here, sir.

1262
01:39:00,380 --> 01:39:02,170
好，告诉杜立特尔小姐 好吗？
Good. Tell Miss Doolittle, will you?

1263
01:39:02,280 --> 01:39:05,610
真的要告诉杜立特尔小姐 我打赌她那件礼服根本不合身
Tell Miss Doolittle indeed. l'll bet you that damned gown doesn't fit.

1264
01:39:05,710 --> 01:39:07,980
我警告过你不该找法国设计师
l warned you about these French designers.

1265
01:39:08,080 --> 01:39:11,020
该找英国的 法国不跟我们同国
We should have gone to an English shop. They would've been on our side.

1266
01:39:11,120 --> 01:39:13,210
喝一杯吗？ 不用，谢谢
-Have a glass of port? -No, thank you.

1267
01:39:20,000 --> 01:39:24,300
你有确信她能够记住 你所教的一切吗？
Are you so sure this girl will retain everything you've hammered into her?

1268
01:39:24,770 --> 01:39:26,530
我们只有等着看了
Well, we shall see.

1269
01:39:26,800 --> 01:39:28,200
如果她失败了呢？
Suppose she doesn't?

1270
01:39:29,570 --> 01:39:31,160
这场打赌我就输了
l lose my bet.

1271
01:39:31,270 --> 01:39:34,940
真受不了你那从容自负的态度
There's one thing l can't stand about you, that's your confounded complacency.

1272
01:39:35,040 --> 01:39:36,870
尤其是在这紧要关头 又关系这么多的金额
At a moment like this, with so much at stake...

1273
01:39:36,980 --> 01:39:39,970
你竟然还不需要喝一杯
it's utterly indecent that you don't need a glass of port.

1274
01:39:42,350 --> 01:39:45,880
关于那女孩呢？ 你好像完全不在乎她
And what about the girl? You act as though she doesn't matter at all.

1275
01:39:46,190 --> 01:39:48,780
胡说，平克林，她当然很重要
Rubbish, Pickering. Of course she matters.

1276
01:39:49,190 --> 01:39:51,590
你以为我花心血是为了什么？
What do you think l've been doing all these months?

1277
01:39:51,690 --> 01:39:54,860
有什么能比这更令人欣慰
What could possibly matter more than to take a human being...

1278
01:39:55,260 --> 01:39:59,170
彻底改变一个人 让她能有新的谈吐方式
and change her into a different human being by creating a new speech for her?

1279
01:39:59,570 --> 01:40:05,230
这完全消弭了阶级之间 灵魂之间的障碍
lt's filling up the deepest gap that separates class from class... and soul from soul.

1280
01:40:05,910 --> 01:40:09,170
哦，她对我而言很重要的
Oh, she matters immensely.

1281
01:40:30,270 --> 01:40:32,760
杜立特尔小姐，你真漂亮
Miss Doolittle, you look beautiful.

1282
01:40:33,440 --> 01:40:34,990
谢谢，平克林上校
Thank you, Colonel Pickering.

1283
01:40:35,100 --> 01:40:36,660
你不觉得吗，席根斯？
Don't you think so, Higgins?

1284
01:40:39,740 --> 01:40:42,570
非常好，真的非常好
Not bad. Not bad at all.

1285
01:41:39,170 --> 01:41:52,340
“中场休息”

1286
01:41:57,490 --> 01:42:07,790
“间奏曲”

1287
01:43:42,520 --> 01:43:45,250
大师！...
Maestro! Maestro!

1288
01:43:47,160 --> 01:43:48,130
你不记得我了？
Don't you remember me?

1289
01:43:48,230 --> 01:43:49,820
不记得，你是谁？
No. Who the devil are you?

1290
01:43:49,930 --> 01:43:53,490
我是你最棒的第一位门生
l'm your pupil. Your first, your greatest, your best pupil.

1291
01:43:53,600 --> 01:43:56,330
我是神童索腾卡帕锡
l'm Zoltan Karpathy, that marvelous boy.

1292
01:43:57,470 --> 01:43:59,460
我让你名闻于全欧洲
l made your name famous throughout Europe.

1293
01:43:59,580 --> 01:44:01,410
你教我语言学 你不可能忘记我的
You teach me phonetics. You cannot forget me.

1294
01:44:01,510 --> 01:44:02,980
你为何不理个发？
Why don't you have your hair cut?

1295
01:44:03,080 --> 01:44:06,170
我并没有像你一般的风采
l don't have your imposing appearance, your figure, your brow.

1296
01:44:06,280 --> 01:44:09,150
如果我把头发剪短了 就没有人会注意到我
lf l had my hair cut, nobody would notice me.

1297
01:44:09,250 --> 01:44:10,910
这些是你从哪儿弄来的？
Where did you get all of these old coins?

1298
01:44:11,020 --> 01:44:13,010
是我对语言贡献得来的勋章
These are decorations for languages.

1299
01:44:13,120 --> 01:44:15,020
今晚特兰夕法尼亚女王要来此
The Queen of Transylvania is here this evening.

1300
01:44:15,120 --> 01:44:17,790
我是她在官方场合 不可或缺的要角
l'm indispensable to her at these official international parties.

1301
01:44:17,890 --> 01:44:21,090
我精通32种语言 我认识欧洲的每一个人
l speak 32 languages. l know everyone in Europe.

1302
01:44:21,200 --> 01:44:23,460
没有骗子可以逃过我的法眼
No imposter can escape my detection.

1303
01:44:23,570 --> 01:44:26,130
卡帕锡教授
Professor Karpathy.

1304
01:44:27,570 --> 01:44:28,760
希腊的大使
The Greek ambassador.

1305
01:44:29,740 --> 01:44:31,040
希腊，我的天啊！
Greek, my foot!

1306
01:44:31,140 --> 01:44:33,700
他假装不会说英语 但是骗不了我的
He pretends not to know any English, but he cannot deceive me.

1307
01:44:33,810 --> 01:44:36,000
他是约克夏钟表制造商的儿子
He's the son of a Yorkshire watchmaker.

1308
01:44:36,950 --> 01:44:42,710
他的英语说得棒极了 无法掩饰他真实的身份
He speaks English so villainously that he cannot utter a word... without betraying his origin.

1309
01:44:42,790 --> 01:44:46,280
我帮他假装 但他们都得付出代价
l help him pretend, but l make him pay through the nose. l make them all pay.

1310
01:44:46,390 --> 01:44:49,520
打扰了，女王陛下要你上楼去
Excuse me, sir, you are wanted upstairs. Her Excellency asked for you.

1311
01:44:49,790 --> 01:44:50,690
失陪了
Excuse me,

1312
01:45:09,680 --> 01:45:11,670
萨克森子爵和子爵夫人
Viscount and Viscountess Saxon.

1313
01:45:15,080 --> 01:45:17,950
约克夏男爵和男爵夫人
Baron and Baroness of Yorkshire.

1314
01:45:19,660 --> 01:45:22,490
盖爵士和苏格兰夫人
Sir Guy and Lady Scot Auckland.

1315
01:45:42,340 --> 01:45:44,510
笛米诺伯爵和伯爵夫人
The Count and Countess Demereau.

1316
01:45:45,250 --> 01:45:47,740
希尔亚子爵和子爵夫人
The Viscount and Viscountess Hillyard.

1317
01:45:47,920 --> 01:45:50,780
李察兰斯夫妇
Mr. and Mrs. Richard Lanser.

1318
01:45:51,420 --> 01:45:54,010
克兰德夫妇
Lord and Lady Clanders.

1319
01:45:54,690 --> 01:45:57,590
伊莱莎杜立特尔小姐 平克林上校
Miss Eliza Doolittle, Colonel Pickering.

1320
01:45:57,930 --> 01:46:01,490
伊莱莎杜立特尔小姐 平克林上校
Miss Eliza Doolittle. Colonel Pickering.

1321
01:46:01,930 --> 01:46:03,920
席根斯教授 晚安
Professor Higgins.

1322
01:46:04,400 --> 01:46:06,390
阁下 杜立特尔小姐
-Your Excellency. -Miss Doolittle.

1323
01:46:06,600 --> 01:46:07,860
你好？
How do you do?

1324
01:46:07,970 --> 01:46:10,270
晚安，上校 晚安
-Good evening, Colonel. -Good evening.

1325
01:46:10,670 --> 01:46:14,870
上校，她真是个迷人的女孩
What an enchanting young lady you have with you this evening.

1326
01:46:15,280 --> 01:46:16,470
她是谁？
Well, who is she?

1327
01:46:16,880 --> 01:46:20,610
哦，是我的远房亲戚 席根斯，失陪一下
Oh, a cousin of mine. And Higgins. Excuse me.

1328
01:46:20,950 --> 01:46:22,040
席根斯教授
Professor Higgins.

1329
01:46:22,350 --> 01:46:26,550
一付不可捉摸的样子 好像她住在花园中
Such a faraway look, as if she's always lived in a garden.

1330
01:46:26,760 --> 01:46:28,920
她是和花园有点关系
So she has. A sort of garden.

1331
01:46:57,820 --> 01:47:01,260
亨利必须马上送伊莱莎回家 这里有位语言专家
Henry must take Eliza home at once. There's a language expert here.

1332
01:47:01,360 --> 01:47:04,520
专门揭穿冒牌者的身份 你说什么？
-Sort of, you know, imposterologist. -l beg you pardon?

1333
01:47:05,290 --> 01:47:07,320
那位和平克林上校一起的女孩
The young lady with Colonel Pickering....

1334
01:47:07,960 --> 01:47:09,520
查出她是谁
Find out who she is.

1335
01:47:09,770 --> 01:47:10,930
我的荣幸
With pleasure.

1336
01:47:11,500 --> 01:47:13,660
目前的场面一触即发
The whole situation is highly explosive.

1337
01:47:19,810 --> 01:47:22,370
索腾，再告诉我一些 有关希腊大使的事
Tell me, Zoltan, some more about the Greek ambassador.

1338
01:47:22,480 --> 01:47:26,000
很乐意，但请先介绍我 和那位优雅的女孩认识
Gladly, but first l would love you to present me to this glorious creature.

1339
01:47:26,110 --> 01:47:27,950
他真的是从约克夏出身的吗？
Does he really come from Yorkshire?

1340
01:47:37,190 --> 01:47:40,180
特兰夕法尼亚女王陛下...
Her Majesty, the Queen of Transylvania...

1341
01:47:40,300 --> 01:47:43,460
和太子殿下葛戈
and His Royal Highness Prince Gregor.

1342
01:48:29,580 --> 01:48:32,070
迷人，真迷人
Charming. Quite charming.

1343
01:48:33,420 --> 01:48:35,180
这位是杜立特尔小姐，女王
Miss Doolittle, Madam.

1344
01:50:11,280 --> 01:50:13,940
杜立特尔小姐 我的皇子想和你跳舞
Miss Doolittle, my son would like to dance with you.

1345
01:51:09,470 --> 01:51:12,000
伊莱沙
Eliza

1346
01:53:21,000 --> 01:53:22,830
真的是大功告成
Absolutely fantastic.

1347
01:53:26,310 --> 01:53:27,740
一群傻瓜蛋
A lot of tomfoolery.

1348
01:53:27,840 --> 01:53:29,830
没想到如此地成功
lt was an immense achievement.

1349
01:53:29,950 --> 01:53:31,210
怎样呢，席根斯先生？
Well, Mr. Higgins?

1350
01:53:31,880 --> 01:53:35,010
胜利，皮尔斯太太 全面的胜利
A triumph, Mrs. Pearce. A total triumph.

1351
01:53:35,280 --> 01:53:38,880
席根斯，你真是棒极了
Higgins, you were superb, absolutely superb.

1352
01:53:38,990 --> 01:53:42,950
说实话 难道你真的都不紧张？
Tell us the truth now, weren't you a little bit nervous once or twice?

1353
01:53:43,060 --> 01:53:44,790
整晚完全不紧张吗？
Not during the whole evening?

1354
01:53:44,890 --> 01:53:46,550
直到我知道我赢了之后
Not when l saw we were going to win.

1355
01:53:46,660 --> 01:53:48,420
我感觉像熊在笼子晃来晃去 无所事事
l felt like a bear in a cage hanging about.

1356
01:53:48,530 --> 01:53:50,400
没想到如此成功
lt was an immense achievement.

1357
01:53:50,500 --> 01:53:53,130
如果我没自信 我两个月前就放弃了
lf l hadn't backed myself to do it, l'd have given it up two months ago.

1358
01:53:53,230 --> 01:53:54,960
真的是大功告成
Absolutely fantastic.

1359
01:53:55,070 --> 01:53:56,590
真的，一群傻瓜蛋
Yes, a lot of tomfoolery.

1360
01:53:56,710 --> 01:53:58,640
席根斯，我向你致敬
Higgins, l salute you.

1361
01:53:58,740 --> 01:54:01,470
那些傻瓜根本不知道 他们做了什么傻事
The silly people don't know their own silly business.

1362
01:54:01,580 --> 01:54:04,640
今晚，老兄，你办到了...
Tonight, old man, you did it You did it, you did it

1363
01:54:04,750 --> 01:54:07,610
你说你办得到，你真的办到了
You said that you would do it And indeed you did

1364
01:54:07,720 --> 01:54:10,690
我以为你会懊恼 我怀疑你办得到
l thought that you would rue it l doubted you'd do it

1365
01:54:10,790 --> 01:54:13,750
但是现在我必须承认你成功了
But now l must admit it That succeed you did

1366
01:54:13,960 --> 01:54:16,580
你应得到勋章或加封进爵
You should get a medal Or be even made a knight

1367
01:54:16,690 --> 01:54:19,420
哦，没什么大不了
Oh, it was nothing, really nothing

1368
01:54:20,060 --> 01:54:22,960
你独自一人克服 迎面而来的障碍
All alone you hurdled Every obstacle in sight

1369
01:54:23,060 --> 01:54:26,230
慢着...我不能独享这份荣耀
Now wait, now wait Give credit where it's due

1370
01:54:26,330 --> 01:54:28,860
你也有很大的功劳
A lot of the glory goes to you

1371
01:54:29,570 --> 01:54:32,560
但是你才是办到的人 你办到了...
But you're the one who did it Who did it, who did it

1372
01:54:32,670 --> 01:54:37,010
是你坚毅不服输的精神
As sturdy as Gibraltar Not a second did you falter There's no doubt about it

1373
01:54:37,080 --> 01:54:40,510
你办到了！
You did it!

1374
01:54:43,590 --> 01:54:47,850
我得承认今晚我很紧张 以为自己会惊吓而死
l must have aged a year tonight At times l thought l'd die of fright

1375
01:54:47,960 --> 01:54:50,650
没有放松过一分钟
Never was there a momentary lull

1376
01:54:51,830 --> 01:54:55,850
当我们一进去 我立刻知道成功在握
Shortly after we came in l saw at once we'd easily win

1377
01:54:55,960 --> 01:54:58,690
在那之后，我更确定赢了
And after that l found it deadly dull

1378
01:55:00,000 --> 01:55:02,200
你们真该在场听那些惊叹声
You should have heard The ''oohs ''and ''aahs ''

1379
01:55:02,300 --> 01:55:04,290
每个人都在猜她是谁
Everyone wondering who she was

1380
01:55:04,410 --> 01:55:07,770
他们好像从没见过女人
You'd think they'd never seen A lady before

1381
01:55:07,940 --> 01:55:13,140
当王子要求见她时
And when the Prince of Transylvania Asked to meet her

1382
01:55:13,250 --> 01:55:17,280
伸出手腕带她进舞池
And gave his arm To lead her to the floor

1383
01:55:18,120 --> 01:55:21,380
我就告诉他，你办到了...
l said to him.: ''You did it You did it, you did it''

1384
01:55:21,490 --> 01:55:24,620
他们认为她气质非凡 举止高贵
They thought she was ecstatic And so damned aristocratic

1385
01:55:24,730 --> 01:55:30,430
没人想到这完全是你的杰作
And they never knew That you did it

1386
01:55:32,630 --> 01:55:34,500
真是感谢索腾卡帕锡
Thank goodness for Zoltan Karpathy.

1387
01:55:34,600 --> 01:55:36,800
如果不是有他 我还真的很无聊呢
lf it hadn't been for him l would've died of boredom.

1388
01:55:36,910 --> 01:55:39,170
卡帕锡？那可怕的匈牙利人 他在那里？
Karpathy? That dreadful Hungarian? Was he there?

1389
01:55:39,270 --> 01:55:42,140
对，他在那里耍他的老把戏
Yes, he was there all right and up to his old tricks.

1390
01:55:42,540 --> 01:55:47,380
那无赖利用语言科学 专门来敲诈行骗别人
That blackguard Who uses the science of speech More to blackmail and swindle than teach

1391
01:55:48,220 --> 01:55:54,020
他想用他的专业 来查出杜立特尔小姐是谁
He made it the devilish business of his To find out who this Miss Doolittle is

1392
01:55:55,020 --> 01:55:59,790
只要我们一转身 他像猎犬般地在身边
Every time we looked around There he was That hairy hound from Budapest

1393
01:56:01,760 --> 01:56:06,170
根本就不放过我们，真烦人
Never leaving us alone Never have l ever known A ruder pest

1394
01:56:08,100 --> 01:56:12,510
后来认为不让他有机会接近她 这岂不是太傻了
Finally l decided it was foolish Not to let him have his chance with her

1395
01:56:14,410 --> 01:56:18,400
所以我就退一边 让他和她来共舞
So l stepped aside And let him dance with her

1396
01:56:20,180 --> 01:56:25,550
他就尽力使出全身的魅力
Oozing charm from every pore He oiled his way around the floor

1397
01:56:25,650 --> 01:56:29,990
用尽方法 只想拆穿她的真面目
Every trick that he could play He used to strip her mask away

1398
01:56:30,430 --> 01:56:34,520
音乐结束 他很得意以为自己赢了
And when at last the dance was done He glowed as if he knew he'd won

1399
01:56:35,330 --> 01:56:38,460
满脸微笑迫不及待想开口
And with a voice too eager And a smile too broad

1400
01:56:38,930 --> 01:56:42,630
她告诉宴会女主人 她是个冒牌货
He announced to the hostess That she was a fraud

1401
01:56:43,370 --> 01:56:44,670
不！
No!

1402
01:56:50,110 --> 01:56:54,340
她的英语太标准 那就表示她是外国人
''Her English is too good, ''he said ''That clearly indicates that she is foreign

1403
01:56:56,620 --> 01:57:01,280
有人曾说英国本地人 不可能讲那种标准的英语
''Whereas others are instructed ln their native language ''English people aren't

1404
01:57:02,960 --> 01:57:07,620
虽然她可以向语言专家学英语
''And although she may have studied with An expert dialectician and grammarian

1405
01:57:09,800 --> 01:57:14,790
但我还是可以探出 她的真实身份
''l can tell that she was born

1406
01:57:15,470 --> 01:57:16,870
她是匈牙利人
''Hungarian ''

1407
01:57:18,740 --> 01:57:21,440
不只是匈牙利人还有贵族血统
Not only Hungarian but of royal blood

1408
01:57:22,310 --> 01:57:24,300
她是一位公主
She is a princess

1409
01:57:24,680 --> 01:57:28,480
他说她的血统比多瑙河还清
''Her blood, ''he said ''ls bluer than the Danube is or ever was

1410
01:57:28,620 --> 01:57:31,550
脸上充满了贵族气质
''Royalty is absolutely written on her face

1411
01:57:31,650 --> 01:57:34,750
她以为骗得了我但其实不然
''She thought l was taken in But actually l never was

1412
01:57:34,860 --> 01:57:37,690
她怎认为可以骗得了自己同胞
''How could she deceive Another member of her race?

1413
01:57:38,390 --> 01:57:42,890
他说我知道全世界各国语言
''l know each language on the map'' Said he

1414
01:57:43,000 --> 01:57:47,300
她是不折不扣的匈牙利公主
''And she's Hungarian As the first Hungarian Rhapsody''

1415
01:57:48,700 --> 01:57:54,770
太精彩了

1416
01:57:55,310 --> 01:57:59,140
恭喜，席根斯教授
Congratulations, Professor Higgins

1417
01:57:59,550 --> 01:58:03,010
祝贺你光荣的胜利
For your glorious victory

1418
01:58:03,280 --> 01:58:07,050
恭喜，席根斯教授
Congratulations, Professor Higgins

1419
01:58:07,460 --> 01:58:10,910
你将会名留青史
You'll be mentioned in history

1420
01:58:11,930 --> 01:58:31,340
恭喜，席根斯教授 祝贺你光荣的胜利
Congratulations, Professor HigginsFor your glorious victory

1421
01:58:33,620 --> 01:58:35,810
感谢上帝，一切都结束了
Well, thank God, that's over.

1422
01:58:36,350 --> 01:58:38,820
我终于可以安眠了
Now l can go to bed without dreading tomorrow.

1423
01:58:41,490 --> 01:58:43,790
晚安，席根斯先生 晚安，皮尔斯太太
-Good night, Mr. Higgins. -Good night, Mrs. Pearce.

1424
01:58:43,890 --> 01:58:47,760
我也想睡了，晚安，席根斯 真是难忘的一夜
l think l'll turn in, too. Good night, Higgins. lt's been a great occasion.

1425
01:58:47,860 --> 01:58:49,300
晚安，平克林
Good night, Pickering.

1426
01:58:50,400 --> 01:58:51,870
皮尔斯太太？
Mrs. Pearce?

1427
01:58:52,670 --> 01:58:56,870
该死 我要她明早送咖啡不要茶
Damn, l meant to ask her to give me coffee in the morning instead of tea.

1428
01:58:57,510 --> 01:59:00,910
伊莱沙，你留条子给她好吗？ 把灯关掉
Leave a little note for her will you, Eliza. And put out the lights.

1429
01:59:49,090 --> 01:59:51,680
是不是在楼下，哦，真是的
Must be downstairs. Oh, darn it.

1430
01:59:52,060 --> 01:59:53,860
我这些天都没在用脑子
l'll leave my head behind one of these days.

1431
01:59:53,960 --> 01:59:56,160
我到底把拖鞋放哪去了？
What the devil have l done with my slippers?

1432
01:59:59,330 --> 02:00:00,930
这是你的拖鞋！
Here are your slippers!

1433
02:00:02,100 --> 02:00:06,200
拿去
Take

1434
02:00:06,310 --> 02:00:10,210
拿去你的拖鞋 希望你穿上后失去好运
Take your slippers and may you never have a day's luck with them.

1435
02:00:10,850 --> 02:00:14,580
怎么回事？哪里不对劲？
What on Earth? What's the matter? ls anything wrong?

1436
02:00:14,720 --> 02:00:17,650
没什么，你是没什么 我帮你赢了打赌，不是吗？
No, nothing's wrong with you. l won your bet for you, haven't l?

1437
02:00:17,750 --> 02:00:20,590
对你而言是有成就 我根本不重要吧？
That's enough for you! l don't matter, l suppose?

1438
02:00:21,220 --> 02:00:24,820
你帮我赢的？有没有弄错？ 是我自己赢的
You won my bet? You presumptuous insect! l won it!

1439
02:00:24,930 --> 02:00:26,550
你为何用拖鞋丢我？
Why did you throw those slippers at me?

1440
02:00:26,660 --> 02:00:29,930
因为我想丢到你的脸上 杀死你这自私的家伙！
Because l wanted to smash your face. l could kill you, you selfish brute!

1441
02:00:30,030 --> 02:00:32,360
你当初为何不让我 留在贫民窟？
Why didn't you leave me where you picked me up, the gutter?

1442
02:00:32,470 --> 02:00:36,130
你感谢上帝一切都结束了 你现在就要送我回那里去吧？
You thank God it's all over. Now you can throw me back again! Do you?

1443
02:00:36,340 --> 02:00:38,930
哦，原来你已经开始在紧张了
Oh, so the creature's nervous after all?

1444
02:00:42,410 --> 02:00:44,740
收回你的猫爪 你竟敢如此对我？
Claws in, you cat! How dare you show your temper to me?

1445
02:00:44,850 --> 02:00:46,400
安静地坐下！
Sit down and be quiet!

1446
02:00:46,510 --> 02:00:50,210
哦，我会变成如何？...
Oh, what's to become of me? What's to become of me?

1447
02:00:52,320 --> 02:00:55,550
我怎么会知道你会变得如何？ 那和我没关系
How the devil do l know what's to become of you? What does it matter?

1448
02:00:55,620 --> 02:00:58,490
你根本不在乎 我知道你根本不在乎我
You don't care. l know you don't care.

1449
02:00:58,690 --> 02:01:00,850
你根本不管我的死活 我跟你毫无瓜葛
You wouldn't care if l was dead. l'm nothing to you.

1450
02:01:00,960 --> 02:01:02,830
比拖鞋还不如
Not as much as them slippers.

1451
02:01:02,930 --> 02:01:03,990
这些拖鞋！
Those slippers!

1452
02:01:04,100 --> 02:01:07,760
这些拖鞋 我想现在根本没什么不同了
Those slippers! l didn't think it meant any difference now.

1453
02:01:11,140 --> 02:01:13,570
你为何突然有如此的举动？
Why have you suddenly begun going on like this?

1454
02:01:14,240 --> 02:01:16,730
请教一下，你是否对这里 任何有不满之处？
May l ask if you complain of your treatment here?

1455
02:01:17,040 --> 02:01:17,740
没有
No

1456
02:01:17,850 --> 02:01:21,110
有人对你不好吗？ 平克林上校还是皮尔斯太太？
Has anybody behaved badly? Colonel Pickering, Mrs. Pearce?

1457
02:01:21,220 --> 02:01:22,480
没有
No

1458
02:01:22,580 --> 02:01:26,140
你不会说是我对你不好吧？
Well you don't pretend that l have treated you badly?

1459
02:01:26,650 --> 02:01:27,350
不是
No

1460
02:01:27,460 --> 02:01:29,450
这样就好
Well, l'm glad to hear that.

1461
02:01:30,560 --> 02:01:33,690
或许因为这几天训练的太累了
Perhaps you're tired after the strain of the day.

1462
02:01:34,060 --> 02:01:36,720
你要吃巧克力吗？
Would you have a chocolate?

1463
02:01:36,830 --> 02:01:39,770
不了，谢谢
No, thank you.

1464
02:01:41,440 --> 02:01:44,890
其实你应该高兴才对 都结束了
Well, it's only natural that you should be anxious, but it's all over now.

1465
02:01:45,440 --> 02:01:47,170
你没什么好担心了
Nothing more to worry about.

1466
02:01:47,410 --> 02:01:50,280
不，是你不必再担心什么了
No, nothing more for you to worry about.

1467
02:01:51,610 --> 02:01:54,480
哦，天啊 我真希望我死掉算了
Oh, God, l wish l was dead.

1468
02:01:54,950 --> 02:01:57,510
为什么？到底是为了什么？
Why? ln heaven's name, why?

1469
02:01:58,390 --> 02:02:02,020
听我说，伊莱莎 所有的烦躁都是个人因素
Now listen to me, Eliza. All this irritation is purely subjective.

1470
02:02:02,490 --> 02:02:04,720
我不了解，我太无知了
l don't understand. l'm too ignorant.

1471
02:02:04,830 --> 02:02:08,060
那只是幻想，并没有什么不对 没有人会伤害你的
lt's just imagination. Nothing's wrong. Nobody's hurting you.

1472
02:02:08,430 --> 02:02:14,170
你上床睡觉，好好哭一场 向上帝祷告，你会感觉好些的
Go to bed and sleep it off. Have a little cry and say your prayers. You'll feel very much more comfortable.

1473
02:02:14,500 --> 02:02:18,270
我听到你的祷告了 感谢上帝，一切都结束
l heard your prayers. ''Thank God it's all over.''

1474
02:02:18,370 --> 02:02:20,070
难道你不感谢上帝 这一切都结束了吗？
Don't you thank God it's all over?

1475
02:02:20,170 --> 02:02:22,570
你现在自由了 可以做你想做的任何事情
Now you're free, and you can do what you like.

1476
02:02:22,680 --> 02:02:25,980
哦，我适合做什么？ 你让我以后能做什么呢？
Oh, what am l fit for? What have you left me fit for?

1477
02:02:26,510 --> 02:02:29,380
我要何去何从？ 我会变成怎样呢？
Where am l to go? What am l to do?

1478
02:02:29,920 --> 02:02:32,110
我会变成怎样呢？
And what's to become of me?

1479
02:02:33,090 --> 02:02:36,060
哦，原来你是为此事烦恼
Oh, that's what's worrying you, is it?

1480
02:02:37,530 --> 02:02:39,460
如果我是你 我才不会担心这个呢
l wouldn't worry about that if l were you.

1481
02:02:39,560 --> 02:02:43,720
我相信你要找栖身之所 应该不会很困难的
l'm sure you won't have any difficulty in settling yourself somewhere or other.

1482
02:02:46,730 --> 02:02:48,900
我没想到你终究还是会离开的
l didn't quite realize you were going away.

1483
02:02:50,440 --> 02:02:52,370
你有可能会结婚
You might marry, you know.

1484
02:02:52,770 --> 02:02:56,640
伊莱莎，并非每个男人 都像我和上校一样抱独身主义
You see, Eliza, all men are not confirmed old bachelors like me and the Colonel.

1485
02:02:56,780 --> 02:02:59,770
大部分的男人都会想结婚 可怜的家伙
Most men are the marrying sort, poor devils.

1486
02:03:00,520 --> 02:03:04,250
你长的还不错 事实上你还真的很美
You're not bad-looking. You're really quite a pleasure to look at sometimes.

1487
02:03:04,390 --> 02:03:07,620
当然不是现在，因为你哭了 你就像母夜叉一样，但是...
Not now, when you've been crying. You look like the very devil, but...

1488
02:03:07,690 --> 02:03:13,090
在平常的时候 你是相当吸引人的
when you're all right and quite yourself you're what l would call attractive.

1489
02:03:14,060 --> 02:03:16,390
你现去睡觉，好好地休息 早上起来之后...
Go to bed, have a good night's rest, get up in the morning...

1490
02:03:16,500 --> 02:03:19,730
看看镜中的自己 你就会感觉好一点了
and have a look at yourself in the glass. You won't feel so bad.

1491
02:03:24,740 --> 02:03:28,330
也许我母亲 可以找到不错的年青人
l daresay, my mother might find some fellow or other who would do very well.

1492
02:03:28,680 --> 02:03:30,770
我们已经超越层级了
We were above that in Covent Garden.

1493
02:03:30,880 --> 02:03:32,350
你是什么意思？
What do you mean?

1494
02:03:32,550 --> 02:03:35,070
我卖花，但我不卖身
l sold flowers, l didn't sell myself.

1495
02:03:35,850 --> 02:03:38,940
现在你把我变成淑女 我什么都不能卖了
Now you've made a lady of me, l'm not fit to sell anything else.

1496
02:03:39,050 --> 02:03:41,680
哦，胡说，伊莱莎 不要看扁人们的关系
Oh, tosh, Eliza. Don't insult human relations...

1497
02:03:41,790 --> 02:03:44,820
只会存在买卖的关系
by dragging all that cant about buying and selling into it.

1498
02:03:44,930 --> 02:03:46,990
你不喜欢他，你不必嫁给他
Don't marry the fellow if you don't want to.

1499
02:03:47,090 --> 02:03:48,690
那我又能做些什么呢？
What else am l to do?

1500
02:03:48,800 --> 02:03:53,130
哦，很多事情 你以前想要开花店的啊
Oh, there are lots of things. What about the old idea of a florist shop?

1501
02:03:53,230 --> 02:03:56,260
我相信平克林可以帮你的忙 他很有钱
l'm sure Pickering'd set you up in one. He's got lots of money.

1502
02:03:56,370 --> 02:04:02,500
今晚你穿戴的所有饰物 价值二百英镑都是他付的
He'll pay for all those togs you're wearing. And that with the hire of the jewelry'll make a big hole in 200 pounds.

1503
02:04:02,710 --> 02:04:05,010
哦，拜托，你不会有事的
Oh, come on now. You'll be all right.

1504
02:04:06,250 --> 02:04:09,150
我必须去睡了 我真的太想睡了
Well, l must be off to bed. l'm really devilish sleepy.

1505
02:04:10,750 --> 02:04:12,950
我不是在找东西吗？是什么？
l was looking for something. What was it?

1506
02:04:13,120 --> 02:04:14,310
你的拖鞋
Your slippers.

1507
02:04:14,860 --> 02:04:17,590
哦，对了，你用它打我
Oh, yes, of course. You shied them at me.

1508
02:04:18,730 --> 02:04:21,190
在你离开之前，先生
Before you go, sir.

1509
02:04:24,770 --> 02:04:27,760
我身上的衣服是属于我 还是平克林上校？
Do my clothes belong to me or to Colonel Pickering?

1510
02:04:28,840 --> 02:04:31,030
怎么会是平克林上校的呢？
What the devil use would they be to Pickering?

1511
02:04:31,140 --> 02:04:32,940
你干嘛在三更半夜问这些？
Why bother about that in the middle of the night?

1512
02:04:33,040 --> 02:04:34,670
我要知道我能带走些什么？
What may l take away with me?

1513
02:04:34,780 --> 02:04:36,900
我不想被指控偷窃
l don't want to be accused of stealing.

1514
02:04:37,850 --> 02:04:39,110
偷窃？
Stealing?

1515
02:04:40,010 --> 02:04:42,920
你不该这样说的 那显示占有的欲望
You shouldn't have said that. That shows a want of feeling.

1516
02:04:43,420 --> 02:04:45,480
抱歉 我只是个普通无知的村妇
l'm sorry. l'm only a common,

1517
02:04:45,590 --> 02:04:47,490
我这种身份必须很小心
ignorant girl and in my station l have to be careful.

1518
02:04:47,590 --> 02:04:50,790
我们之间该不会 出现喜欢彼此的情感
There can't be any feelings between the likes of you and the likes of me.

1519
02:04:50,890 --> 02:04:53,880
所以请告诉我，什么是我的 而那些不是？
Please, will you tell me what belongs to me and what doesn't?

1520
02:04:55,060 --> 02:04:57,460
如果你喜欢房子里 所有的东西都拿走
Take the whole damned houseful if you want.

1521
02:04:57,700 --> 02:05:00,030
除了那宝石是租来的以外 你满意了吗？
Except the jewelry. That's hired. Will that satisfy you?

1522
02:05:00,130 --> 02:05:01,260
请等一下
Stop, please.

1523
02:05:03,800 --> 02:05:06,600
请把它带走，放在安全的地方
Will you take these to your room and keep them safe?

1524
02:05:07,680 --> 02:05:10,270
我不想要冒它们被偷的险
l don't want to run the risk of them being missed.

1525
02:05:12,180 --> 02:05:15,670
哦，拿给我吧！ 如果这些是我的又不是宝石...
Oh, hand them over! lf these belonged to me and not the jeweler, l'd...

1526
02:05:15,780 --> 02:05:18,340
我会用它塞入 你那不知感恩的喉咙里
l'd ram them down your ungrateful throat.

1527
02:05:18,650 --> 02:05:22,920
这戒指不是租的 是你在布莱顿买给我的
The ring isn't the jeweler's. lt's the one you bought me in Brighton.

1528
02:05:24,060 --> 02:05:25,620
我现在不想要了
l don't want it now.

1529
02:05:28,900 --> 02:05:30,560
别打我！
Don't you hit me!

1530
02:05:31,030 --> 02:05:34,200
打你？你这个可恶的人 你竟敢这样说！
Hit you? You infamous creature! How dare you suggest such a thing!

1531
02:05:34,300 --> 02:05:36,930
是你要打我的 你存心要伤害我的
lt's you who've hit me. You've wounded me to the heart.

1532
02:05:37,040 --> 02:05:40,630
我真高兴我还保有我的心
l'm glad. l've got a little of my own back anyhow.

1533
02:05:42,010 --> 02:05:45,380
你令我生气 以前很少会发生这种事
You've caused me to lose my temper. That's hardly happened to me before.

1534
02:05:45,480 --> 02:05:48,240
今晚我不想讨论了，我要睡了
l don't wish to discuss it further tonight. l'm going to bed.

1535
02:05:48,350 --> 02:05:50,720
你最好自己留条子 给皮尔斯太太有关咖啡的事...
Leave your own note for Mrs. Pearce about the coffee...

1536
02:05:50,820 --> 02:05:52,580
我是不会帮你写的
for it won't be done by me!

1537
02:05:52,690 --> 02:05:56,280
去他的皮尔斯太太 去他的咖啡还有去你的！
Damn Mrs. Pearce, damn the coffee and damn you!

1538
02:05:57,530 --> 02:06:05,230
去我自己还慷慨用我的知识 帮助一位无情无义的流浪儿
Damn my own folly for having lavished my hard-earned knowledge... and the treasure of my regard and intimacy on a heartless guttersnipe!

1539
02:06:56,320 --> 02:07:01,020
等着看，席根斯，等着看
Just you wait, 'Enry 'lggins Just you wait!

1540
02:07:02,890 --> 02:07:07,120
你会后悔 但你流泪也来不及了
You'll be sorry But your tears will be too late

1541
02:07:09,130 --> 02:07:16,130
你将会失败而无人可哭诉
You will be the one it's done to And you'll have no one to run to

1542
02:07:16,670 --> 02:07:18,230
等着看
Just you wait

1543
02:07:46,800 --> 02:07:52,430
我以前常在这条路上漫步
l have often walked Down this street before

1544
02:07:52,540 --> 02:07:58,340
但是脚下的步伐毫无特别
But the pavement always stayed Beneath my feet before

1545
02:07:58,450 --> 02:08:04,110
瞬时间我的思绪飞扬在空中
All at once am l Several stories high

1546
02:08:04,220 --> 02:08:10,050
知道这是你所住的街道
Knowing l'm on the street Where you live

1547
02:08:10,160 --> 02:08:15,960
丁香花不是在市中心吗？
Are there lilac trees ln the heart of town?

1548
02:08:16,060 --> 02:08:21,900
听到云雀在城市中鸣叫？
Can you hear a lark ln any other part of town?

1549
02:08:22,000 --> 02:08:27,770
是否会迷倒所有的住户？
Does enchantment pour Out of every door?

1550
02:08:27,880 --> 02:08:33,750
不，只是因你住在此
No, it's just On the street where you live

1551
02:08:33,850 --> 02:08:45,920
知道你在附近 那感觉多么强烈
And, oh, the towering feeling Just to know Somehow you are near

1552
02:08:46,030 --> 02:08:51,120
无法抗拒的情感
The overpowering feeling

1553
02:08:51,230 --> 02:08:57,330
因为你随时都会出现
That any second You may suddenly appear

1554
02:08:57,440 --> 02:09:02,030
我不在乎别人的注视
People stop and stare They don't--

1555
02:09:07,480 --> 02:09:08,450
亲爱的
Darling.

1556
02:09:09,950 --> 02:09:11,650
佛雷狄，你在这里干什么？
Freddy, whatever are you doing here?

1557
02:09:11,750 --> 02:09:15,620
没事，我大部分的晚上都在此 因为我来这里会很快乐
Nothing. l spend most of my nights here. lt's the only place where l'm happy.

1558
02:09:15,720 --> 02:09:17,320
不要取笑我，杜立特尔小姐
Don't laugh at me, Miss Doolittle.

1559
02:09:17,420 --> 02:09:21,360
别叫我杜立特尔小姐，听到没 叫我伊莱莎就好
Don't you call me ''Miss Doolittle,'' do you hear? Eliza's good enough for me.

1560
02:09:23,700 --> 02:09:26,960
哦，佛雷狄，你认为我是个 无情无义的流浪儿吗？
Oh, Freddy, you don't think l'm a heartless guttersnipe, do you?

1561
02:09:27,370 --> 02:09:30,430
亲爱的，你怎会如此讲呢？ 你知道我对你的感受
Darling, how could you imagine such a thing? You know how l feel.

1562
02:09:30,540 --> 02:09:33,970
我一天写好几次的信告诉你 一张接一张
l've written two and three times a day telling you. Sheets and sheets.

1563
02:09:34,070 --> 02:09:37,530
你一开口，声音如同歌唱一般
Speak And the world is full of singing

1564
02:09:37,650 --> 02:09:42,880
我心也飞上天空 比鸟飞的还高
And l am winging Higher than the birds

1565
02:09:42,980 --> 02:09:46,780
你一摸，我的心就崩溃
Touch And my heart begins to crumble

1566
02:09:46,890 --> 02:09:50,720
天也塌了，亲爱的，我...
The heavens tumble Darling, and l'm--

1567
02:09:50,820 --> 02:09:53,950
文字...我痛恨文字
Words, words, words l'm so sick of words

1568
02:09:54,060 --> 02:09:57,220
我每天都听文字 先是他，现在是你
l get words all day through First from him, now from you

