Ding dong, the bells are gonna chime

1732
02:21:28,220 --> 02:21:32,320
来吧，打开酒瓶，让我们狂饮
Come on, pull out the stopper Let's have a whopper

1733
02:21:32,430 --> 02:21:36,450
但一定要准时送我到教堂
But get me to the church on time

1734
02:21:36,560 --> 02:21:40,430
他今早一定要到教堂
He's got to be there in the mornin'

1735
02:21:40,530 --> 02:21:44,470
穿着体面，整整齐齐
Spruced up and lookin'in his prime

1736
02:21:44,570 --> 02:21:48,470
女士们，过来亲我 表现你们会有多想念我
Girls, come and kiss me Show how you'll miss me

1737
02:21:48,580 --> 02:21:52,010
但一定要准时送我到教堂
But get me to the church on time

1738
02:21:52,110 --> 02:21:55,880
如果我还在跳舞 就把地板拆掉
lf l am dancin' Roll up the floor

1739
02:21:55,980 --> 02:22:00,180
如果我在吹口哨 把我轰出门外
lf l am whistlin' Me out the door

1740
02:22:00,290 --> 02:22:04,660
因为他一早就要结婚了

1741
02:22:04,760 --> 02:22:08,660
教堂的钟声就要响起

1742
02:22:08,760 --> 02:22:12,600
迷昏我，锁住我 帖邮票把我寄走
Drug me or jail me Stamp me and mail me

1743
02:22:12,700 --> 02:22:14,670
但是送我到教堂
But get me to the church

1744
02:22:14,770 --> 02:22:16,600
送他到教堂
Get him to the church

1745
02:22:16,700 --> 02:22:22,610
一定要把我准时送到教堂
For God's sake Get me to the church on time

1746
02:22:30,950 --> 02:22:34,750
女士们，过来亲他 表现你们会有多想念他
Girls, come and kiss him Show how they miss him

1747
02:22:34,850 --> 02:22:38,850
但一定要准时把他送到教堂
But get him to the church on time

1748
02:22:47,230 --> 02:22:50,900
尽情地玩闹但不要失去理智
Kick up a rumpus But don't lose the compass

1749
02:22:51,000 --> 02:22:54,440
但一定要准时把他送到教堂
And get him to the church on time

1750
02:22:54,540 --> 02:22:58,530
如果我在飞翔，把我射下来
lf l am flyin' Then shoot me down

1751
02:22:58,650 --> 02:23:03,050
如果我还在求爱 把那个女人轰出城去
lf l am wooin' Get her out of town

1752
02:23:03,150 --> 02:23:07,180
他今早就要结婚了
He's gettin'married in the mornin'

1753
02:23:07,290 --> 02:23:11,220
教堂的钟声就要响起
Ding dong, the bells are gonna chime

1754
02:23:11,320 --> 02:23:15,260
高兴的人可以把桌子掀掉
Some bloke who's able Lift up the table

1755
02:23:15,360 --> 02:23:19,490
但一定要准时送我到教堂
But get me to the church on time

1756
02:23:56,140 --> 02:24:02,970
星辰也摇晃地回家睡觉了
Starlight is reelin' Home to bed now

1757
02:24:03,080 --> 02:24:10,140
晨曦也渐渐升起
Mornin'is smearin' up the sky

1758
02:24:10,250 --> 02:24:13,520
城市也苏醒
London is wakin'

1759
02:24:13,620 --> 02:24:16,950
也到破晓时分
Daylight is breakin'

1760
02:24:17,060 --> 02:24:19,820
祝好运，好友
Good luck, old chum

1761
02:24:19,930 --> 02:24:21,660
祝健康
Good health

1762
02:24:21,760 --> 02:24:26,820
再见
Goodbye

1763
02:24:26,930 --> 02:24:34,900
我今早就要结婚了
l'm gettin'married in the mornin'

1764
02:24:35,010 --> 02:24:41,610
教堂的钟声就要响起
Ding dong, the bells are gonna chime

1765
02:24:41,710 --> 02:24:45,840
为我欢呼致意让我离开吧
Hail and salute me Then haul off and boot me

1766
02:24:45,950 --> 02:24:49,890
但是送他到教堂，送他到教堂
But get him to the church Get him to the church

1767
02:24:49,990 --> 02:25:05,340
但一定要准时把他送到教堂
For God's sake Get him to the church on time

1768
02:25:06,340 --> 02:25:09,080
平克林...她有说要将她的衣服 送到哪里吗？
Didn't she say where to send her clothes?

1769
02:25:09,080 --> 02:25:10,980
我告诉过你了，先生 她全带走了
l told you, sir, she took them all with her.

1770
02:25:11,080 --> 02:25:15,150
平克林，发生了奇怪的事 伊莱莎，跑走了 跑走？ 跑走了
Here's a confounded thing. Eliza's bolted. Bolted!

1771
02:25:15,250 --> 02:25:18,550
昨晚皮尔斯太太让她走了 竟然完全没有告诉我
Last night Mrs. Pearce let her go without telling me a thing about it!

1772
02:25:18,650 --> 02:25:20,740
我怎么办？ 我早上要喝茶不喝咖啡
What am l to do? l got tea this morning instead of coffee.

1773
02:25:20,850 --> 02:25:22,650
我不知东西放在那 我有哪些会议要参加
l don't know where anything is, what my appointments are.

1774
02:25:22,760 --> 02:25:25,690
伊莱莎知道 该死，她走了啊！
-Eliza'd know. -Damn it, she's gone!

1775
02:25:25,790 --> 02:25:28,020
你们两位是否 昨晚把她吓着了？
Did either of you gentlemen frighten her last night?

1776
02:25:28,130 --> 02:25:30,120
我们根本没有跟她说话 你也在场
We hardly said a word to her. You were there.

1777
02:25:30,230 --> 02:25:31,820
我去睡觉后你又凶她了吗？
Did you bully her after l went to bed?

1778
02:25:31,930 --> 02:25:33,690
相反地，她用拖鞋丢我
She threw the slippers at me.

1779
02:25:33,800 --> 02:25:38,100
我根本没有惹她 我还没说话拖鞋就打到我的头
l never gave her the slightest provocation. The slippers came bang at my head before l uttered a word.

1780
02:25:38,170 --> 02:25:42,230
她用最恶毒的话骂我 我吓一跳，我完全不懂
She used the most disgraceful language. l was shocked! l don't understand it.

1781
02:25:42,340 --> 02:25:44,810
我们对她照顾周详 她自己也承认
We always gave her every consideration. She admitted it.

1782
02:25:44,910 --> 02:25:45,740
我毫无概念！
l'm dashed!

1783
02:25:45,850 --> 02:25:49,340
哦，平克林，快想些办法啊 什么办法？
Oh, Pickering, for God's sake, stop being dashed and do something!

1784
02:25:49,480 --> 02:25:52,080
打电话报警啊，不都是这样吗
Phone the police. What are they there for in heaven's name?

1785
02:25:52,190 --> 02:25:54,680
席根斯 不能把伊莱莎的名字告诉警察
You can't give Eliza's name to the police...

1786
02:25:54,790 --> 02:25:56,880
好像她是小偷或偷了东西似的
as if she were a thief or a lost umbrella.

1787
02:25:56,990 --> 02:26:01,260
为何不行？我要找到那女孩 她是我的，我付了5英镑
But why not? l want to find the girl. She belongs to me. l paid five pounds for her.

1788
02:26:01,960 --> 02:26:04,620
没错，请帮我接苏格兰警场
Quite right. Hello. Scotland Yard, please?

1789
02:26:05,060 --> 02:26:06,960
给我杯咖啡，好吗？ 是的
Get me some coffee, would you please?

1790
02:26:07,070 --> 02:26:09,300
苏格兰警场
Scotland Yard?

1791
02:26:09,400 --> 02:26:17,780
对不起，我是平克林上校 住温普街27号A
l beg your pardon, yes. This is, this is Colonel Pickering speaking. 27 A Wimpole Street.

1792
02:26:18,280 --> 02:26:20,510
我要报案，是人口失踪
l want to report a missing person.

1793
02:26:21,180 --> 02:26:24,380
伊莱莎杜立特尔小姐
Miss Eliza Doolittle.

1794
02:26:24,480 --> 02:26:25,450
年约21岁
About 21 .

1795
02:26:26,650 --> 02:26:29,520
哦，身高我想是五尺七英寸
Oh, l should say about 5 foot 7.

1796
02:26:30,760 --> 02:26:34,720
眼睛的颜色？ 让我想想，眼睛...
Her eyes? Let me think now. Her eyes. Her eyes--

1797
02:26:35,060 --> 02:26:36,820
褐色 褐色
-Brown. -Brown.

1798
02:26:39,570 --> 02:26:44,260
头发颜色？哦，天啊 很难区分...
Her hair? Oh, good Lord. Well, sort of nondescript neutral sort of--

1799
02:26:44,370 --> 02:26:46,000
褐色...！
Brown, brown, brown!

1800
02:26:46,110 --> 02:26:48,570
你你听到了吗？褐色...是的
You heard what he said? Brown, brown, brown, yes.

1801
02:26:48,880 --> 02:26:51,310
不...这里是...
No, no, no. This is her residence. 27 A--

1802
02:26:51,440 --> 02:26:55,240
是，大约是今天凌晨 三点至四点间
Yes, about between 3:00 and 4:00 this morning, l understand.

1803
02:26:56,420 --> 02:27:00,350
不...她不是亲戚，不是，什么
No, no, no.... No, she's no relation, no.

1804
02:27:00,450 --> 02:27:03,250
她就是我们很好的朋友
Well, just let's call her a good friend, shall we?

1805
02:27:03,860 --> 02:27:05,120
你说什么？
l beg your pardon?

1806
02:27:05,430 --> 02:27:08,160
听着，我不喜欢你问的问题
Listen to me, my man, l don't like the tenor of that question.

1807
02:27:08,260 --> 02:27:10,820
她在此干嘛是我们的私事
What the girl does here is our affair.

1808
02:27:11,930 --> 02:27:15,420
你们的职责就是尽快找到她
Your affair is to get her back so she can continue doing it.

1809
02:27:16,040 --> 02:27:17,530
我真的昏头了
Well, l'm dashed!

1810
02:27:20,070 --> 02:27:23,040
真不知道她为何要走？
What in all, in heaven Could have prompted her to go?

1811
02:27:23,140 --> 02:27:25,240
在舞会表现成功之后
After such a triumph at the ball

1812
02:27:26,180 --> 02:27:27,670
何事让她沮丧？
What could have depressed her?

1813
02:27:27,780 --> 02:27:31,380
她执着些什么？ 我真的毫无头绪
What could have possessed her? l cannot understand the wretch at all

1814
02:27:33,920 --> 02:27:37,950
席根斯，我在内政部有朋友 或许他能帮忙
Higgins, l have an old school chum at the Home Office. Perhaps he could help.

1815
02:27:38,120 --> 02:27:39,610
我该打个电话给他
Think l'll give him a ring.

1816
02:27:41,530 --> 02:27:44,290
请接白厅7244号
Whitehall: 7244, please.

1817
02:27:46,900 --> 02:27:49,420
女人根本毫无理性可言
Women are irrational That's all there is to that

1818
02:27:49,640 --> 02:27:51,900
脑袋装的是浆糊
Their heads are full of Cotton, hay and rags

1819
02:27:52,740 --> 02:27:56,470
女人是令人恼怒，令人生气 犹豫不决，工于心计
They're nothing but exasperating lrritating, vacillating, calculating

1820
02:27:56,580 --> 02:27:59,310
激动，疯狂，易怒的臭婆娘
Agitating, maddening And infuriating hags

1821
02:28:00,850 --> 02:28:04,180
我想和布鲁斯特巴金先生说话
l want to speak to Mr. Brewster Budgin, please.

1822
02:28:04,980 --> 02:28:06,420
好的，我会等的
Yes, l'll wait.

1823
02:28:11,790 --> 02:28:16,160
平克林 为何女人不能像男人一般？
Pickering, why can't a woman be more like a man?

1824
02:28:16,700 --> 02:28:17,820
你说什么？
l beg your pardon?

1825
02:28:18,430 --> 02:28:21,730
是啊 为何女人不能像男人一般？
Yes, why can't a woman be more like a man?

1826
02:28:22,640 --> 02:28:29,100
男人诚实，公正，高贵，公平
Men are so honest, so thoroughly square Eternally noble, historically fair

1827
02:28:29,210 --> 02:28:32,370
是谁在赢得胜利 会鼓励手下败将？
Who, when you win Will always give your back a pat?

1828
02:28:32,510 --> 02:28:35,710
为何女人不能像那样呢？
Why can't a woman be like that?

1829
02:28:36,250 --> 02:28:39,620
为何都要相互模仿？
Why does every one do What the others do?

1830
02:28:39,720 --> 02:28:42,980
难道女人没有大脑？
Can't a woman learn to use her head?

1831
02:28:43,090 --> 02:28:45,990
为何她们都照母亲的指示做？
Why do they do everything Their mothers do?

1832
02:28:46,090 --> 02:28:49,490
为何她们长大不能像父亲？
Why don't they grow up Well, like their father instead?

1833
02:28:49,600 --> 02:28:52,660
为何女人不能向男人学习？
Why can't a woman take after a man?

1834
02:28:52,770 --> 02:28:55,960
男人很和o，容易取悦
Men are so pleasant, so easy to please

1835
02:28:56,070 --> 02:28:59,300
当你跟他们一起，都很轻松
Whenever you're with them You're always at ease

1836
02:28:59,410 --> 02:29:01,810
如果我一下子没跟你说话 你会觉得受轻视吗？
Would you be slighted lf l didn't speak for hours?

1837
02:29:01,910 --> 02:29:02,740
当然不会

1838
02:29:02,840 --> 02:29:04,810
如果我喝一两杯 你会发怒吗？
Would you be livid lf l had a drink or two?

1839
02:29:04,910 --> 02:29:05,900
别胡扯

1840
02:29:06,010 --> 02:29:08,280
如果我没送你花 你会不会心碎？
Would you be wounded lf l never sent you flowers?

1841
02:29:08,380 --> 02:29:09,040
不会吧！

1842
02:29:09,150 --> 02:29:12,350
为何女人不能像你一般？
Well, why can't a woman be like you?

1843
02:29:13,120 --> 02:29:15,920
或许百万人中会有一人不同
One man in a million may shout a bit

1844
02:29:16,490 --> 02:29:19,250
多多少少会有一个瑕疵
Now and then There's one with slight defects

1845
02:29:19,790 --> 02:29:22,390
或许有一人的真诚值得你怀疑
One perhaps whose truthfulness You doubt a bit

1846
02:29:22,500 --> 02:29:26,450
但是大多数而言 我们是优秀的男人
But by and large We are a marvelous sex

1847
02:29:26,570 --> 02:29:29,560
为何女人不能向男人学习？
Why can't a woman take after a man?

1848
02:29:29,670 --> 02:29:32,830
因为男人是友善的 有善良的性质，善解人意
Cause men are so friendly Good-natured and kind

1849
02:29:32,940 --> 02:29:36,270
找不到这么好的朋友
A better companion You never will find

1850
02:29:36,380 --> 02:29:38,870
如果我迟点回家吃晚饭 你会对我咆哮吗？
lf l were hours late for dinner Would you bellow?

1851
02:29:38,980 --> 02:29:39,710
当然不会

1852
02:29:39,810 --> 02:29:41,800
如果我忘记你的生日 你会大惊小怪吗？
lf l forgot your silly birthday Would you fuss?

1853
02:29:41,910 --> 02:29:42,740
别胡扯

1854
02:29:42,850 --> 02:29:45,040
如果我跟另外一个人出去 你会抱怨吗？
Would you complain lf l took out another fellow?

1855
02:29:45,150 --> 02:29:45,950
不会！

1856
02:29:46,050 --> 02:29:49,390
为何女人不能像我们一般
Well, why can't a woman be like us?

1857
02:29:52,430 --> 02:29:53,720
布鲁斯特巴金先生在吗？
ls Mr. Brewster Budgin there?

1858
02:29:54,930 --> 02:29:59,330
布鲁斯，哦，布鲁斯 你绝对猜不着我是谁
Bruzzie. Oh, Bruzzie, you'll never guess who this is.

1859
02:30:00,570 --> 02:30:04,300
没错，天啊，你的记性真好
You're quite right, it is. Good heavens. By George, what a memory.

1860
02:30:05,440 --> 02:30:08,410
你好吗，布鲁斯？ 真高兴听到你的声音
How are you, Bruzzie? Nice to hear your voice.

1861
02:30:09,180 --> 02:30:12,140
什么？真的吗 30年没见了，布鲁斯？
What? You don't say. Has it really been 30 years, Bruzzie?

1862
02:30:12,950 --> 02:30:14,170
没错，相隔太远了
Quite right. Yes, oceans of water.

1863
02:30:14,280 --> 02:30:16,540
听着，布鲁斯 有件事要拜托你
Listen, Bruzzie, l'll tell you why l rang up.

1864
02:30:16,650 --> 02:30:20,380
有件不太好的事发生 我可否去找你？
Something rather unpleasant happened at this end. Could l come and see you?

1865
02:30:20,490 --> 02:30:22,480
可以，好，我马上过去
Well, l could, yes. Now, straight away?

1866
02:30:22,590 --> 02:30:23,750
对，很好，谢谢
Right. Good. Thank you.

1867
02:30:23,860 --> 02:30:25,920
再见，布鲁斯，非常感谢
Goodbye, Bruzzie. Thank you very much.

1868
02:30:33,400 --> 02:30:36,200
皮尔斯太太，我去内政部一下
Mrs. Pearce, l'm going along to the Home Office.

1869
02:30:36,940 --> 02:30:39,230
我真的很希望你找到她 平克林上校
l do hope you find her, Colonel Pickering.

1870
02:30:39,340 --> 02:30:41,030
席根斯先生很想她的
Mr. Higgins will miss her.

1871
02:30:41,140 --> 02:30:45,370
席根斯先生很想她的？ 管他席根斯先生，我也想念她
Mr. Higgins will miss her, eh? Blast Mr. Higgins, l'll miss her!

1872
02:30:47,580 --> 02:30:48,950
平克林？
Pickering

1873
02:30:51,180 --> 02:30:52,620
平克林？
Pickering

1874
02:30:56,890 --> 02:30:59,120
皮尔斯太太？ 是的，先生
-Mrs. Pearce? -Yes, sir.

1875
02:30:59,390 --> 02:31:00,360
上校去哪里了？
Where's the Colonel?

1876
02:31:00,460 --> 02:31:03,260
他去内政部了
He's gone to the Home Office, sir.

1877
02:31:03,360 --> 02:31:09,460
你看看，我有麻烦他就帮忙 他真是我的好朋友
There you are. l'm disturbed and he runs for help. Now there's a good fellow.

1878
02:31:10,500 --> 02:31:13,770
皮尔斯太太，你是一个女人
Mrs. Pearce, you're a woman.

1879
02:31:14,170 --> 02:31:17,800
为何女人不能像男人一般？
Why can't a woman be more like a man?

1880
02:31:17,910 --> 02:31:21,000
男人如此正派，标准的典型
Men are so decent Such regular chaps

1881
02:31:21,110 --> 02:31:24,280
只要你有麻烦，随时都会帮你
Ready to help you Through any mishaps

1882
02:31:24,380 --> 02:31:27,440
只要你沮丧，随时都会振作你
Ready to buck you up Whenever you are glum

1883
02:31:27,550 --> 02:31:30,990
为何女人不能像男人？
Why can't a woman be a chum?

1884
02:31:31,490 --> 02:31:34,790
为何女人不会思考？
Why is thinking Something women never do?

1885
02:31:34,890 --> 02:31:38,020
为何不会逻辑推理？
And why is logic never even tried?

1886
02:31:38,130 --> 02:31:41,070
只会整理她们的头发
Straightening up their hair ls all they ever do

1887
02:31:41,170 --> 02:31:44,690
为何不整理脑袋里的思绪？
Why don't they straighten up The mess that's inside?

1888
02:31:44,800 --> 02:31:47,860
为何女人的行为不能像男人？
Why can't a woman behave like a man?

1889
02:31:47,970 --> 02:31:51,140
如果我是参加舞会的女人
lf l was a woman Who'd been to a ball

1890
02:31:51,240 --> 02:31:54,440
每个人待我像公主
Been hailed as a princess By one and by all

1891
02:31:54,550 --> 02:31:57,610
我是否会痛哭流涕？
Would l start weeping Like a bathtub overflowing?

1892
02:31:57,720 --> 02:32:00,710
或是无法住在这栋房子里？
Or carry on as if my home Were in a tree?

1893
02:32:00,820 --> 02:32:03,880
我会不说一句走跑走吗？
Would l run off And never tell me where l'm going?

1894
02:32:03,990 --> 02:32:07,690
为何女人不像我呢？
Why can't a woman be like me?

1895
02:32:11,300 --> 02:32:15,760
你是说在你替他完成了 这项不可思议的任务后
You mean that after you'd done this wonderful thing for them... without making a mistake...

1896
02:32:15,840 --> 02:32:17,800
他们只是坐下来 没跟你说一句话？
they just sat there and never said a word?

1897
02:32:17,900 --> 02:32:21,700
没有称赞你，说你有多棒吗？
Never petted you, or admired you, or told you how splendid you'd been?

1898
02:32:21,810 --> 02:32:22,670
一个字都没有
Not a word.

1899
02:32:22,780 --> 02:32:25,740
他们只是互相庆贺 完成了一件多么不可思议的事
They just congratulated each other on how marvelous they'd been.

1900
02:32:25,850 --> 02:32:28,310
然后庆幸这一切都过去了
The next moment, how glad they were it was all over...

1901
02:32:28,410 --> 02:32:30,210
这舞会的过程有多无聊
and what a bore it had all been.

1902
02:32:30,320 --> 02:32:33,340
这太不像话了 我不会只用拖鞋丢他
This is simply appalling. l should not have thrown my slippers at him.

1903
02:32:33,450 --> 02:32:35,440
我会用火戳丢他
l should have thrown the fire irons.

1904
02:32:36,020 --> 02:32:37,050
是谁？
Who's that?

1905
02:32:37,320 --> 02:32:40,020
是亨利，我知道这不会很久的
Henry. l knew it wouldn't be too long.

1906
02:32:41,630 --> 02:32:42,860
要记住...
Now, remember...

1907
02:32:43,730 --> 02:32:47,560
你不只是昨晚跟王子跳舞 现在也要像是公主一般
you not only danced with a prince last night, you behaved like a princess.

1908
02:32:54,940 --> 02:32:57,240
母亲，真令人不解...
Mother, the most confounded thing.... Do you--

1909
02:33:01,210 --> 02:33:02,240
是你！
You!

1910
02:33:02,980 --> 02:33:05,640
午安，席根斯教授 你还好吧？
Good afternoon, Professor Higgins. Are you quite well?

1911
02:33:07,550 --> 02:33:11,820
当然好，你从来没病过 你要喝茶吗？
Of course you are. You are never ill. Would you care for some tea?

1912
02:33:12,460 --> 02:33:15,450
休想和我玩这把戏 是我教你这一切的
Don't you dare try that game on me. l taught it to you.

1913
02:33:15,660 --> 02:33:17,190
起来，跟我回去 别像傻子一样
Get up, come home and stop being a fool.

1914
02:33:17,300 --> 02:33:18,790
你已经惹了不少麻烦
You've caused me enough trouble.

1915
02:33:18,900 --> 02:33:22,890
真的是这样，亨利 没有女人能拒绝这种邀约的
Very nicely put indeed, Henry. No woman could resist such an invitation.

1916
02:33:23,000 --> 02:33:24,770
这些袋子怎么会在这里？
How did this baggage get here?

1917
02:33:24,870 --> 02:33:27,810
伊莱莎今早到这里来看我 我很高兴见到她
Eliza came to see me this morning and l was delighted to have her.

1918
02:33:27,910 --> 02:33:30,640
如果你不能乖乖的 我就要请你离开了
lf you don't promise to behave yourself l must ask you to leave.

1919
02:33:30,740 --> 02:33:36,640
你是说我必须要对我所训练的 菜市场女人举止合宜吗？
You mean, l'm to put on my Sunday manners for this... thing that l created out of the squashed cabbage leaves of Covent Garden?

1920
02:33:36,720 --> 02:33:38,080
我就是这个意思
That's precisely what l mean.

1921
02:33:38,180 --> 02:33:40,150
真是不可理喻！

1922
02:33:40,250 --> 02:33:42,950
你是如何从我儿子那里 学习当个淑女的？
However did you learn good manners with my son around?

1923
02:33:43,560 --> 02:33:49,650
实在很困难，如果不是上校 我无法学会淑女和绅士的相处
lt was very difficult. l should never have known how ladies... and gentlemen behave if it hadn't been for Colonel Pickering.

1924
02:33:52,230 --> 02:33:57,030
他让我感受到 我并非只是个卖花女
He showed me that he felt and thought about me... as if l were something better than a common flower girl.

1925
02:34:00,370 --> 02:34:03,540
席根斯夫人 有许多事情让人们可以学到...
You see, Mrs. Higgins, apart from the things one can pick up...

1926
02:34:04,310 --> 02:34:07,840
淑女和卖花女的差别 并非在言行
the difference between a lady and a flower girl isn't how she behaves...

1927
02:34:07,950 --> 02:34:09,570
而是人们对待她的态度
but how she is treated.

1928
02:34:12,650 --> 02:34:18,060
在教授眼中我永远是个卖花女 因为他待我像卖花女
l shall always be a flower girl to Professor Higgins... because he always treats me as a flower girl and always will.

1929
02:34:19,460 --> 02:34:24,460
而在上校眼中我永远是个淑女 因为他待我像是淑女
l know l'll always be a lady to Colonel Pickering... because he always treats me as a lady and always will.

1930
02:34:29,870 --> 02:34:31,300
亨利，不要在那里磨牙
Henry, don't grind your teeth.

1931
02:34:31,400 --> 02:34:34,200
夫人，主教来了 要我带他去花园吗？
The bishop is here, Madam. Shall l show him into the garden?

1932
02:34:34,310 --> 02:34:36,710
主教和教授？天啊，不要！
The bishop and the professor? Good heavens, no!

1933
02:34:36,910 --> 02:34:38,670
我会被逐出教会的
l should be excommunicated.

1934
02:34:39,010 --> 02:34:40,670
我在书房见他
l'll see him in the library.

1935
02:34:41,710 --> 02:34:47,050
伊莱莎，如果我儿子不讲理 你可以赶他出去
Eliza, if my son starts breaking up things... l give you full permission to have him evicted.

1936
02:34:47,350 --> 02:34:51,720
亨利，我建议你谈两个话题 天气和健康
Henry dear, l suggest you stick to two subjects: the weather and your health.

1937
02:35:19,420 --> 02:35:21,410
你可以在自由意愿下回去
You've had a bit of your own back, as you say.

1938
02:35:21,520 --> 02:35:25,150
你玩够了没，你可以讲理了吗 还是要继续玩下去？
Have you had enough and are you going to be reasonable or do you want any more?

1939
02:35:25,260 --> 02:35:27,020
你是要我回去帮你拿拖鞋
You want me back to pick up your slippers...

1940
02:35:27,130 --> 02:35:30,120
忍受你的脾气 然后料理你的杂事
and put up with your tempers and fetch and carry for you.

1941
02:35:30,230 --> 02:35:31,820
我没有说我要你回来
l didn't say l wanted you back at all.

1942
02:35:31,930 --> 02:35:33,490
真的吗？ 那我们还谈个什么劲？
lndeed? Then what are we talking about?

1943
02:35:33,600 --> 02:35:35,260
是谈你，不是谈我
Well, about you, not about me.

1944
02:35:35,500 --> 02:35:37,770
如果你回来 我对你的态度与往常一般
lf you come back you'll be treated as you've always been.

1945
02:35:37,870 --> 02:35:40,300
我不需要改变我的态度
l can't change my nature or my manners.

1946
02:35:40,410 --> 02:35:43,200
我的态度 跟平克林上校的是一样
My manners are exactly the same as Colonel Pickering's.

1947
02:35:43,340 --> 02:35:46,610
那不是事实 他对待卖花女好似伯爵夫人
That's not true. He treats a flower girl as if she were a duchess.

1948
02:35:47,280 --> 02:35:49,470
而我对待伯爵夫人 好似个卖花女
And l treat a duchess as if she was a flower girl.

1949
02:35:49,580 --> 02:35:51,380
哦，原来如此，一视同仁
Oh, l see. The same to everybody.

1950
02:35:51,480 --> 02:35:58,520
没错，重点不是 对某种人态度会有不同
You see, the great secret is not a question of good manners... or bad manners or any particular sort of manners...

1951
02:35:59,020 --> 02:36:02,720
而是对所有人的态度都相同
but having the same manner for all human souls.

1952
02:36:04,260 --> 02:36:06,660
问题不是我对你很无礼
The question is not whether l treat you rudely...

1953
02:36:06,770 --> 02:36:09,790
而是你有看过我对任何人好吗
but whether you've ever heard me treat anyone else better.

1954
02:36:10,300 --> 02:36:12,430
我不在乎你如何对待我
l don't care how you treat me.

1955
02:36:12,540 --> 02:36:15,170
我不介意你用粗话骂我 我不介意自己丢脸
l don't mind your swearing at me. l shouldn't mind a black eye.

1956
02:36:15,270 --> 02:36:18,680
我曾经体会过 但是我不喜欢被忽视！
l've had one before this. But l won't be passed over!

1957
02:36:18,780 --> 02:36:20,640
别挡路 我不会因你而停下来改变
Get out of my way, for l won't stop for you.

1958
02:36:20,750 --> 02:36:22,650
你说的我好像是部公车
You talk about me as though l was a motorbus.

1959
02:36:22,750 --> 02:36:26,910
你就是公车 只会来回的开不管乘客是谁
So you are a motorbus. All bounce and go and no consideration for anybody.

1960
02:36:27,420 --> 02:36:30,150
别以为我没有你就无法生存
But l can get along without you. Don't you think l can't!

1961
02:36:30,260 --> 02:36:32,280
我知道你办得到 我说过你行的
l know you can. l told you, you could.

1962
02:36:36,100 --> 02:36:38,330
你从未想过，我觉得...
You've never wondered, l suppose, whether...

1963
02:36:38,760 --> 02:36:40,990
我是否能没有你呢？
whether l could get along without you?

1964
02:36:42,400 --> 02:36:45,430
别想要改变我的想法 你必须要做到
Don't you try to get around me. You'll have to.

1965
02:36:46,640 --> 02:36:48,900
所以我可以，没有你或任何人 我都可以活得下去
So l can, without you or any soul on Earth.

1966
02:36:52,410 --> 02:36:56,810
我会想念你的，伊莱莎 我从你身上也学了不少东西
l shall miss you, Eliza. l've learned something from your idiotic notions.

1967
02:36:57,280 --> 02:36:59,950
我必须承认我由衷地感激
l confess that humbly and gratefully.

1968
02:37:02,790 --> 02:37:05,150
你的留声机里有我的声音
Well, you have my voice on your gramophone.

1969
02:37:05,260 --> 02:37:09,520
寂寞的时候可以打开听听 不会伤感的
When you feel lonely without me you can turn it on. lt has no feelings to hurt.

1970
02:37:11,260 --> 02:37:14,200
我却无法敞开你的心灵
Well, l can't turn your soul on.

1971
02:37:16,670 --> 02:37:18,930
哦，你真是个魔鬼
Oh, you are a devil!

1972
02:37:19,910 --> 02:37:24,710
你还真会伤女孩的心
You can twist the heart in a girl just as easily... as some can twist her arms to hurt her.

1973
02:37:25,040 --> 02:37:26,740
我还回去干什么？
What am l to come back for?

1974
02:37:27,180 --> 02:37:29,240
为了乐趣，所以我才选了你
For the fun of it. That's why l took you on.

1975
02:37:29,350 --> 02:37:31,870
如果我不照你意思做 我就会被你赶出去
You may throw me out tomorrow if l don't do everything you want.

1976
02:37:31,980 --> 02:37:35,610
但是我没照你的意思做事 你也可以马上离开我
Yes. And you may walk out tomorrow if l don't do everything you want.

1977
02:37:35,720 --> 02:37:36,880
去和我父亲住一起吗？
And live with my father?

1978
02:37:36,990 --> 02:37:39,320
是，或去卖花 还是你宁愿和上校结婚
Yes, or sell flowers. Would you rather marry Pickering?

1979
02:37:39,430 --> 02:37:43,290
如果你向我求婚我就嫁给你 起码年纪相近
l wouldn't marry you if you asked me and you're nearer my age then what he is.

1980
02:37:43,760 --> 02:37:46,230
我喜欢说什么我就说 你已经不是我老师了
l'll talk as l like. You're not my teacher now.

1981
02:37:46,770 --> 02:37:49,230
结婚不是我想要的 你不用这样想
That's not what l want and don't you think it is.

1982
02:37:49,670 --> 02:37:51,900
我有许多人在追求我
l've always had chaps enough wanting me that way.

1983
02:37:52,000 --> 02:37:55,060
佛雷狄希尔 一天就写好几封信给我
Freddy Hill writes me twice and three times a day. Sheets and sheets.

1984
02:37:55,170 --> 02:37:58,870
搞半天，原来你要我 像他对你一般痴情
ln short, you want me to be as infatuated about you as he is, is that it?

1985
02:37:59,240 --> 02:38:03,240
不是，我不是要你如此对待我
No, l don't. That's not the sort of feeling l want from you.

1986
02:38:04,320 --> 02:38:05,840
我只求你待我亲切一些
l want a little kindness.

1987
02:38:06,690 --> 02:38:09,980
我知道我是微不足道的卖花女 你是丰富学识的绅士
l know l'm a common, ignorant girl, and you're a book-learned gentleman...

1988
02:38:10,090 --> 02:38:12,250
但我不是你脚下的烂泥
but l'm not dirt under your feet.

1989
02:38:12,790 --> 02:38:17,920
我所做的并非是为了物质享受
What l done...what l did was not for the taxis and the dresses...

1990
02:38:18,200 --> 02:38:22,260
只是因为我们在一起 相处的很愉快，我就...
but because we were pleasant together and l come to...came...

1991
02:38:23,200 --> 02:38:24,600
关心你
to care for you.

1992
02:38:25,240 --> 02:38:26,570
并非想要跟你结婚
Not to want you to make love to me...

1993
02:38:26,670 --> 02:38:29,300
也没忘记你我身份的悬殊 但是...
and not forgetting the difference between us, but...

1994
02:38:30,080 --> 02:38:31,940
只希望我们能更像朋友一样
more friendly like.

1995
02:38:33,950 --> 02:38:36,240
当然，我的想法也和你一样
Well, of course. That's how l feel.

1996
02:38:36,820 --> 02:38:40,620
上校也如此想 伊莱莎，你真傻
And how Pickering feels. Eliza, you're a fool!

1997
02:38:40,720 --> 02:38:42,080
这样回答太不合宜了
That's not the proper answer.

1998
02:38:42,190 --> 02:38:43,880
除非你变聪明 否则还是这样的回答
lt's the only answer till you stop being a idiot.

1999
02:38:43,990 --> 02:38:46,120
如果你要成为淑女 就必须独立自主
lf you want to be a lady, you must stop feeling neglected...

2000
02:38:46,230 --> 02:38:50,790
如果男人不会在你身边哭诉 不会让你丢脸
if the men don't spend half their time sniveling over you... and the other half giving you black eyes.

2001
02:38:50,860 --> 02:38:53,660
你认为我冷淡 没有感情，自私，是吗？
You find me cold, unfeeling, selfish, don't you?

2002
02:38:53,800 --> 02:38:55,630
去跟你喜欢的人在一起
Off with you to the sort of people you like.

2003
02:38:55,730 --> 02:39:00,500
嫁给感情丰富的贪婪有钱人 用厚嘴唇亲你，用大靴子踢你
Marry a sentimental hog with lots of money... and thick lips to kiss you, and thick boots to kick you.

2004
02:39:00,570 --> 02:39:03,470
如果你无法知足常乐 千万不要乐极生悲
lf you can't appreciate what you've got, you'd better get what you can appreciate.

2005
02:39:03,740 --> 02:39:06,910
我说不赢你 你永远有理由反驳我
l can't talk to you. You always turn everything against me.

2006
02:39:07,010 --> 02:39:08,570
我永远都是错的
l'm always in the wrong.

2007
02:39:09,150 --> 02:39:13,380
别太有自信 你可以如此践踏和贬低我
Don't be too sure you have me under your feet... to be trampled on and talked down.

2008
02:39:13,490 --> 02:39:16,510
我要嫁给佛雷狄 一旦我有能力养他就会嫁给他
l'll marry Freddy, l will, as soon as l'm able to support him.

2009
02:39:17,220 --> 02:39:18,620
佛雷狄
Freddy

2010
02:39:18,890 --> 02:39:21,090
那可怜的家伙 连跑腿的小事都作不了
That poor devil who couldn't get a job as an errand boy...

2011
02:39:21,190 --> 02:39:23,130
他还敢尝试要娶你？
even if he had the guts to try for it?

2012
02:39:23,230 --> 02:39:26,990
女人，你还不明白？ 你已经有资格嫁给国王了
Woman, don't you understand? l have made you a consort for a king!

2013
02:39:27,170 --> 02:39:30,140
佛雷狄爱我 在我心中他就是个国王
Freddy loves me. That makes him king enough for me.

2014
02:39:30,270 --> 02:39:33,200
我不要他去工作 他不像我做惯苦力的事情
l don't want him to work. He wasn't brought up to do it as l was.

2015
02:39:33,310 --> 02:39:34,740
我要去当老师
l'll go and be a teacher.

2016
02:39:35,440 --> 02:39:37,430
你能教些什么东西？
What'll you teach, in heaven's name?

2017
02:39:37,540 --> 02:39:40,240
你所教我的，我可以教语言学
What you taught me. l'll teach phonetics.

2018
02:39:44,450 --> 02:39:48,890
我可以当那个匈牙利人的助手
l'll offer myself as an assistant to that brilliant Hungarian.

2019
02:39:49,590 --> 02:39:53,350
那个骗子，冒牌货 无知的马屁精？
What, that imposter? That humbug? That toadying ignoramus?

2020
02:39:53,660 --> 02:39:55,790
教他我发明的方法？
Teach him my methods, my discoveries?

2021
02:39:55,890 --> 02:39:58,490
你再往那个方向做一步 我就拧断你的脖子！
You take one step in that direction, l'll wring your neck!

2022
02:39:58,600 --> 02:40:02,360
拧死我，我在乎什么？ 我早知道有一天你会打我
Wring away! What do l care? l knew you'd strike me one day.

2023
02:40:05,340 --> 02:40:08,270
这个真的整倒你了吧，席根斯
That's done you, 'Enry 'lggins, it 'as.

2024
02:40:08,370 --> 02:40:11,600
我才不管你的霸道 或是你的大话
Now, l don't care for your bullyin' an' your big talk.

2025
02:40:12,750 --> 02:40:14,610
我真的是太傻了
What a fool l was

2026
02:40:14,710 --> 02:40:16,510
真是一个超级大傻瓜
What a dominated fool

2027
02:40:16,620 --> 02:40:19,410
竟以为你是天与地
To think you were the Earth and sky

2028
02:40:20,020 --> 02:40:21,680
我真的是太傻了
What a fool l was

2029
02:40:21,790 --> 02:40:23,580
真是呆头呆脑
What an addle-pated fool

2030
02:40:23,690 --> 02:40:27,850
我真是个大笨蛋
What a mutton-headed dolt was l

2031
02:40:28,030 --> 02:40:36,760
错了，朋友，你不是我的全部
No, my reverberating friend You are not the beginning and the end

2032
02:40:38,900 --> 02:40:40,700
你这冒失的野丫头！
You impudent hussy!

2033
02:40:40,810 --> 02:40:45,270
你的思想谈吐 都是我赐给你的
There's not an idea in your head or a word in your mouth that l haven't put there.

2034
02:40:46,580 --> 02:40:51,910
没有你春天依旧来
There'll be spring every year Without you

2035
02:40:52,020 --> 02:40:55,680
没有你英国依然在
England still will be here Without you

2036
02:40:55,790 --> 02:40:59,590
树果依然茂盛，海岸仍旧存在
There'll be fruit on the tree And a shore by the sea

2037
02:40:59,690 --> 02:41:03,460
没有你下午茶照常
There'll be crumpets and tea Without you

2038
02:41:03,560 --> 02:41:07,160
没有你艺术与音乐盛况依旧
Art and music will thrive Without you

2039
02:41:07,270 --> 02:41:10,960
没有你济慈作品仍在
Somehow Keats will survive Without you

2040
02:41:11,070 --> 02:41:18,640
没有你西班牙平原照常下雨
And there still will be rain On that plain down in Spain Even that will remain Without you

2041
02:41:18,740 --> 02:41:24,550
没有你我也可活下去
l can do Without you

2042
02:41:25,220 --> 02:41:32,390
我口齿伶俐的朋友
You, dear friend Who talk so well

2043
02:41:32,490 --> 02:41:39,450
你可以去哈特福特，赫里福 和汉普郡
You can go to Hartford, Hereford and Hampshire

2044
02:41:39,570 --> 02:41:43,060
没有你国家依旧运行
They can still rule the land Without you

2045
02:41:43,170 --> 02:41:46,760
没有你温莎堡依旧屹立
Windsor Castle will stand Without you

2046
02:41:46,870 --> 02:41:52,670
没有你一切都会顺利
And without much ado We can all muddle through Without you!

2047
02:41:52,780 --> 02:41:55,180
你这个厚颜无耻的野丫头！
You brazen hussy!

2048
02:41:55,280 --> 02:41:59,410
没有你潮汐依旧
Without your pulling it The tide comes in

2049
02:41:59,520 --> 02:42:03,450
没有你自转依旧
Without your twirling it The Earth can spin

2050
02:42:03,560 --> 02:42:08,750
没有你浮云依旧
Without your pushing them The clouds roll by

2051
02:42:08,860 --> 02:42:14,360
如果没有你这些依旧 我也可以没有你
lf they can do without you, Ducky So can l

2052
02:42:14,470 --> 02:42:17,770
没有你我不孤独
l shall not feel alone Without you

2053
02:42:17,870 --> 02:42:21,470
没有你我可以自立
l can stand on my own Without you

2054
02:42:21,570 --> 02:42:26,030
所以回到你的巢穴里 我只能...
So go back in your shell l can do bloody well--

2055
02:42:26,140 --> 02:42:30,080
老天啊，我真的办到了...
By George, l really did it l did it, l did it

2056
02:42:30,180 --> 02:42:32,780
我说我可以改变一个女人 我真的办到了
l said l'd make a woman And indeed l did

2057
02:42:32,890 --> 02:42:35,650
我知道我办得到，我就知道
l knew that l could do it l knew it, l knew it

2058
02:42:35,750 --> 02:42:38,660
我说我可以改变一个女人 我真的成功了
l said l'd make a woman And succeed l did

2059
02:42:38,760 --> 02:42:40,750
伊莱莎，你真的很不可思议
Eliza, you're magnificent.

2060
02:42:40,860 --> 02:42:43,380
五分前你还是我沉重的负担
Five minutes ago you were a millstone around my neck...

2061
02:42:43,500 --> 02:42:45,490
现在你已充满了活力
and now you're a tower of strength.

2062
02:42:45,600 --> 02:42:47,390
战力的结合
A consort battleship.

2063
02:42:48,600 --> 02:42:50,400
我喜欢你这个样子
l like you this way.

2064
02:42:52,440 --> 02:42:56,270
再见，席根斯教授 你不会再见到我了
Goodbye, Professor Higgins. You shall not be seeing me again.

2065
02:43:09,920 --> 02:43:10,980
母亲！
Mother!

2066
02:43:12,390 --> 02:43:13,450
母亲！
Mother!

2067
02:43:14,260 --> 02:43:16,390
怎么了，亨利？发生什么事？
What is it, Henry? What's happened?

2068
02:43:18,330 --> 02:43:19,490
她走了
She's gone.

2069
02:43:19,600 --> 02:43:21,960
当然，亲爱的 你还在指望什么？
Well, of course, dear. What did you expect?

2070
02:43:25,670 --> 02:43:26,800
我该怎么办？
What am l to do?

2071
02:43:26,940 --> 02:43:28,370
你只好过没有她的日子了
Do without, l suppose.

2072
02:43:30,310 --> 02:43:32,070
我会的
And so l shall.

2073
02:43:35,350 --> 02:43:38,340
如果我能让她燃起怒火
lf the Higgins' oxygen burns up her little lungs...

2074
02:43:38,450 --> 02:43:41,010
让她找适合她的灭火方式
let her seek some stuffiness that suits her.

2075
02:43:42,020 --> 02:43:45,580
她就像猫头鹰一样 讨厌我给的阳光
She's an owl sickened by a few days of my sunshine.

2076
02:43:45,890 --> 02:43:47,860
让她走好了，我不需要她
Let her go. l can do without her.

2077
02:43:47,960 --> 02:43:50,260
我并不需要任何人 我有自己的灵魂
l can do without anyone. l have my own soul!

2078
02:43:50,500 --> 02:43:53,330
我自己求爱的欲火！
My own spark of divine fire!

2079
02:43:57,570 --> 02:43:58,900
干得好，伊莱莎
Bravo, Eliza.

2080
02:44:19,320 --> 02:44:22,490
该死...
Damn, damn, damn, damn

2081
02:44:24,800 --> 02:44:27,260
我已经习惯她的脸庞了
l've grown accustomed to her face

2082
02:44:30,800 --> 02:44:32,930
她几乎是让一天开始的泉源
She almost makes the day begin

2083
02:44:33,940 --> 02:44:37,200
我习惯她的声调 还有她日夜的口哨声
l've grown accustomed to the tune That she whistles night and noon

2084
02:44:37,410 --> 02:44:41,180
她的微笑，蹙眉 她的得意和失望
Her smiles, her frowns Her ups, her downs

2085
02:44:41,280 --> 02:44:43,270
现在成为我生活的一部分
Are second nature to me now

2086
02:44:44,420 --> 02:44:46,680
像是呼吸般不可或缺
Like breathing out and breathing in

2087
02:44:47,790 --> 02:44:51,650
在我们未见面之前 我是非常独立和满足
l was serenely independent and content Before we met

2088
02:44:51,760 --> 02:44:55,660
我当然可以再回复 那种生活方式
Surely l could always be that way again

2089
02:44:57,060 --> 02:45:01,120
但我已习惯了她的模样
And yet l've grown Accustomed to her looks

2090
02:45:01,430 --> 02:45:03,260
习惯她的声音
Accustomed to her voice

2091
02:45:03,870 --> 02:45:08,530
习惯她的脸庞
Accustomed to her face

2092
02:45:22,390 --> 02:45:24,250
嫁给佛雷狄
Marry Freddy.

2093
02:45:24,460 --> 02:45:29,020
多幼稚的想法，多么没良心 缺德，没大脑的事
What an infantile idea. What a heartless, wicked, brainless thing to do.

2094
02:45:29,130 --> 02:45:32,430
但是她会后悔的...
But she'll regret it. She'll regret it.

2095
02:45:32,530 --> 02:45:36,190
在还没发誓前 整件事就注定要失败！
lt's doomed before they even take the vow!

2096
02:45:36,740 --> 02:45:40,540
我可以想像她当 佛雷狄恩斯福特希尔夫人模样
l can see her now Mrs. Freddy Eynsford-Hill

2097
02:45:40,640 --> 02:45:43,230
在一个悲惨的小店里
ln a wretched little flat above a store

2098
02:45:43,710 --> 02:45:46,700
我可以想像她 收银机里没半毛钱
l can see her now, not a penny in the till

2099
02:45:46,810 --> 02:45:49,440
而收款员却不停地敲门
And a bill collector beating at the door

2100
02:45:49,950 --> 02:45:55,610
她想当老师 而最后还是去卖花了
She'll try to teach the things l taught her And end up selling flowers instead

2101
02:45:55,720 --> 02:45:58,250
当她为生活奋力挣扎时
Begging for her bread and water

2102
02:45:58,360 --> 02:46:01,550
她先生却在床上用早餐
While her husband has His breakfast in bed

2103
02:46:04,560 --> 02:46:09,190
再过几年，她的头发就变白
ln a year or so When she's prematurely gray

2104
02:46:09,300 --> 02:46:12,670
粉嫩的脸颊成死槁
And the blossom in her cheek Has turned to chalk

2105
02:46:12,770 --> 02:46:18,980
她回到家一看，她先生就吓跑 高攀有钱的女人私奔了
She'll come home and lo He'll have upped and run away With a social-climbing heiress From New York

2106
02:46:19,180 --> 02:46:20,610
多可怜的伊莱莎
Poor Eliza

2107
02:46:20,710 --> 02:46:22,240
多么地可怕
How simply frightful

2108
02:46:22,350 --> 02:46:24,510
多么地丢人
How humiliating

2109
02:46:24,620 --> 02:46:26,610
多么地令人欣慰
How delightful

2110
02:46:28,950 --> 02:46:31,890
在一个令人心酸的晚上
How poignant it will be On that inevitable night

2111
02:46:31,990 --> 02:46:35,190
她一身破烂又带泪来我家叩门
When she hammers on my door ln tears and rags

2112
02:46:35,290 --> 02:46:38,960
悲惨又孤独，忏悔又懊恼
Miserable and lonely Repentant and contrite

2113
02:46:39,060 --> 02:46:41,760
我该收容她？ 还是让她受尽凌辱？
Will l take her in Or hurl her to the wolves?

2114
02:46:41,870 --> 02:46:44,930
亲切地待她？ 还是给她颜色看？
Give her kindness Or the treatment she deserves?

2115
02:46:45,040 --> 02:46:48,940
该让她回来？ 还是将她赶出去？
Will l take her back Or throw the baggage out?

2116
02:46:51,310 --> 02:46:53,540
我是个心胸宽大的人
Well, l'm a most forgiving man

2117
02:46:53,950 --> 02:46:57,310
不会是也不曾是狠心的人
The sort who never could, ever would

2118
02:46:57,420 --> 02:47:01,320
人同此心，心同此理
Take a position and staunchly never budge

2119
02:47:03,620 --> 02:47:06,110
我是个心胸宽大的人
A most forgiving man

2120
02:47:08,690 --> 02:47:11,130
但我不该收容她！
But l shall never take her back

2121
02:47:11,860 --> 02:47:13,830
如果她跪在地上
lf she were crawling on her knees

2122
02:47:14,600 --> 02:47:17,400
让她哀求 让她受冻，让她呻吟
Let her promise to atone Let her shiver, let her moan

2123
02:47:17,500 --> 02:47:21,840
我会把门重重地关上 让这泼妇冻死
l'll slam the door And let the hellcat freeze

2124
02:47:24,140 --> 02:47:26,300
嫁给佛雷狄
Marry Freddy.

2125
02:47:40,690 --> 02:47:46,150
但是我已经习惯 每天听她向我说早安
But l'm so used to hear her say ''Good morning'' every day

2126
02:47:46,260 --> 02:47:48,790
她的欣喜，她的苦恼
Her joys, her woes

2127
02:47:48,900 --> 02:47:51,560
她的兴奋，她的低落
Her highs, her lows

2128
02:47:51,670 --> 02:47:55,070
现在已经成为我生活的一部分
Are second nature to me now

2129
02:47:55,670 --> 02:47:58,510
像是呼吸般不可或缺
Like breathing out and breathing in

2130
02:47:59,740 --> 02:48:04,270
我真的很庆幸是女人 我才能很容易地忘记她
l'm very grateful she's a woman And so easy to forget

2131
02:48:04,380 --> 02:48:08,550
不会难以忘怀
Rather like a habit One can always break

2132
02:48:10,820 --> 02:48:15,590
然而我却已习惯了她的身影
And yet l've grown Accustomed to the trace

2133
02:48:15,730 --> 02:48:25,430
然而我已习惯了她在的气息
Of something in the air Accustomed to her face

2134
02:50:01,630 --> 02:50:03,690
哦，都很骄傲
Oh, we are proud.

2135
02:50:03,800 --> 02:50:07,200
他不想教人说英语 但是我听到他说过的
He ain't above givin'lessons, not 'im. l 'eard 'im say so.

2136
02:50:07,310 --> 02:50:09,470
我不是来此致意的
l ain't come here to ask for any compliment...

2137
02:50:09,570 --> 02:50:12,630
如果我的钱不够我就去别处
and if my money's not good enough, l can go elsewhere.

2138
02:50:12,710 --> 02:50:13,940
够做什么？
Good enough for what?

2139
02:50:14,050 --> 02:50:16,980
足够支付你上课的钱 懂了吗？
Good enough for you. Now you know, don'tcha?

2140
02:50:17,080 --> 02:50:20,410
我来这里上课的 并且是付学费，别搞错了
l'm come to 'ave lessons, l am. And to pay for 'em, too... make no mistake.

2141
02:50:20,490 --> 02:50:22,180
你想要干什么，女孩？
What is it you want, my girl?

2142
02:50:22,290 --> 02:50:28,390
我想要在花店当专柜小姐
l want to be a lady in a flow'r shop 'stead o' sellin'... at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.

2143
02:50:28,490 --> 02:50:31,760
除非我举止优雅 否则他们不会请我
But they won't take me unless l can talk more genteel.

2144
02:50:31,860 --> 02:50:33,560
他说他能教我
He said he could teach me.

2145
02:50:33,670 --> 02:50:35,690
所以我来付钱请他教
Well, 'ere l am ready to pay,

2146
02:50:35,800 --> 02:50:39,240
不是要来占便宜的 他却如此对我
not askin' any favor, and he treats me as if l was dirt.

2147
02:50:39,340 --> 02:50:43,330
我知道你上课的价钱 所以我准备要付钱
l know what lessons cost as well as you do and l'm ready t'pay.

2148
02:50:43,740 --> 02:50:46,580
因此我只会给一先令 随便你要不要
l won't give more than a shillin'. Take it or leave it.

2149
02:50:47,250 --> 02:50:51,410
这真是无法抗拒 她低俗的如此有趣
lt's almost irresistible. She's so deliciously low...

2150
02:50:52,020 --> 02:50:54,610
真是脏死了，我接受
so horribly dirty. l'll take it.

2151
02:50:55,320 --> 02:50:57,980
我会让她彻底的改头换面
l'll make a duchess of this draggle-tailed guttersnipe.

2152
02:51:00,330 --> 02:51:03,560
我洗了脸洗了手才来的
l washed my face and 'ands before l come, l did.

2153
02:51:12,070 --> 02:51:13,660
伊莱莎
Eliza?

2154
02:51:17,710 --> 02:51:19,970
我那该死的拖鞋在哪里？
Where the devil are my slippers?
